8 /// \file InstrRefBasedImpl.cpp ----
9 /// ----
10 /// This is a separate implementation of LiveDebugValues, see ----
11 /// LiveDebugValues.cpp and VarLocBasedImpl.cpp for more information. ----
12 /// ----
13 /// This pass propagates variable locations between basic blocks, resolving ----
14 /// control flow conflicts between them. The problem is SSA construction, where ----
15 /// each debug instruction assigns the *value* that a variable has, and every ----
16 /// instruction where the variable is in scope uses that variable. The resulting ----
17 /// map of instruction-to-value is then translated into a register (or spill) ----
18 /// location for each variable over each instruction. ----
19 /// ----
20 /// The primary difference from normal SSA construction is that we cannot ----
21 /// _create_ PHI values that contain variable values. CodeGen has already ----
22 /// completed, and we can't alter it just to make debug-info complete. Thus: ----
23 /// we can identify function positions where we would like a PHI value for a ----
24 /// variable, but must search the MachineFunction to see whether such a PHI is ----
25 /// available. If no such PHI exists, the variable location must be dropped. ----
26 /// ----
27 /// To achieve this, we perform two kinds of analysis. First, we identify ----
28 /// every value defined by every instruction (ignoring those that only move ----
29 /// another value), then re-compute an SSA-form representation of the ----
30 /// MachineFunction, using value propagation to eliminate any un-necessary ----
31 /// PHI values. This gives us a map of every value computed in the function, ----
32 /// and its location within the register file / stack. ----
33 /// ----
34 /// Secondly, for each variable we perform the same analysis, where each debug ----
35 /// instruction is considered a def, and every instruction where the variable ----
36 /// is in lexical scope as a use. Value propagation is used again to eliminate ----
37 /// any un-necessary PHIs. This gives us a map of each variable to the value ----
38 /// it should have in a block. ----
39 /// ----
40 /// Once both are complete, we have two maps for each block: ----
41 /// * Variables to the values they should have, ----
42 /// * Values to the register / spill slot they are located in. ----
43 /// After which we can marry-up variable values with a location, and emit ----
44 /// DBG_VALUE instructions specifying those locations. Variable locations may ----
45 /// be dropped in this process due to the desired variable value not being ----
46 /// resident in any machine location, or because there is no PHI value in any ----
47 /// location that accurately represents the desired value. The building of ----
48 /// location lists for each block is left to DbgEntityHistoryCalculator. ----
49 /// ----
50 /// This pass is kept efficient because the size of the first SSA problem ----
51 /// is proportional to the working-set size of the function, which the compiler ----
52 /// tries to keep small. (It's also proportional to the number of blocks). ----
53 /// Additionally, we repeatedly perform the second SSA problem analysis with ----
54 /// only the variables and blocks in a single lexical scope, exploiting their ----
55 /// locality. ----
56 /// ----
57 /// ### Terminology ----
58 /// ----
59 /// A machine location is a register or spill slot, a value is something that's ----
60 /// defined by an instruction or PHI node, while a variable value is the value ----
61 /// assigned to a variable. A variable location is a machine location, that must ----
62 /// contain the appropriate variable value. A value that is a PHI node is ----
63 /// occasionally called an mphi. ----
64 /// ----
65 /// The first SSA problem is the "machine value location" problem, ----
66 /// because we're determining which machine locations contain which values. ----
67 /// The "locations" are constant: what's unknown is what value they contain. ----
68 /// ----
69 /// The second SSA problem (the one for variables) is the "variable value ----
70 /// problem", because it's determining what values a variable has, rather than ----
71 /// what location those values are placed in. ----
72 /// ----
73 /// TODO: ----
74 /// Overlapping fragments ----
75 /// Entry values ----
76 /// Add back DEBUG statements for debugging this ----
77 /// Collect statistics ----
78 /// ----

145 // Limit for the maximum number of stack slots we should track, past which we ----
146 // will ignore any spills. InstrRefBasedLDV gathers detailed information on all ----
147 // stack slots which leads to high memory consumption, and in some scenarios ----
148 // (such as asan with very many locals) the working set of the function can be ----
149 // very large, causing many spills. In these scenarios, it is very unlikely that ----
150 // the developer has hundreds of variables live at the same time that they're ----
151 // carefully thinking about -- instead, they probably autogenerated the code. ----
152 // When this happens, gracefully stop tracking excess spill slots, rather than ----
153 // consuming all the developer's memory. ----
154 static cl::opt ----
155 StackWorkingSetLimit("livedebugvalues-max-stack-slots", cl::Hidden, ----
156 cl::desc("livedebugvalues-stack-ws-limit"), ----
157 cl::init(250)); ----

161 /// Tracker for converting machine value locations and variable values into ----
162 /// variable locations (the output of LiveDebugValues), recorded as DBG_VALUEs ----
163 /// specifying block live-in locations and transfers within blocks. ----
164 /// ----
165 /// Operating on a per-block basis, this class takes a (pre-loaded) MLocTracker ----
166 /// and must be initialized with the set of variable values that are live-in to ----
167 /// the block. The caller then repeatedly calls process(). TransferTracker picks ----
168 /// out variable locations for the live-in variable values (if there _is_ a ----
169 /// location) and creates the corresponding DBG_VALUEs. Then, as the block is ----
170 /// stepped through, transfers of values between machine locations are ----
171 /// identified and if profitable, a DBG_VALUE created. ----
172 /// ----
173 /// This is where debug use-before-defs would be resolved: a variable with an ----
174 /// unavailable value could materialize in the middle of a block, when the ----
175 /// value becomes available. Or, we could detect clobbers and re-specify the ----
176 /// variable in a backup location. (XXX these are unimplemented). ----
177 class TransferTracker { ----
178 public: ----
179 const TargetInstrInfo *TII; ----
180 const TargetLowering *TLI; ----
181 /// This machine location tracker is assumed to always contain the up-to-date ----
182 /// value mapping for all machine locations. TransferTracker only reads ----
183 /// information from it. (XXX make it const?) ----
184 MLocTracker *MTracker; ----
185 MachineFunction &MF; ----
186 bool ShouldEmitDebugEntryValues; ----

189 /// we allow inserting either before or after the point: MBB != nullptr ----
190 /// indicates it's before, otherwise after. ----
191 struct Transfer { ----
192 MachineBasicBlock::instr_iterator Pos; /// Position to insert DBG_VALUes ----
193 MachineBasicBlock *MBB; /// non-null if we should insert after. ----
194 SmallVector Insts; /// Vector of DBG_VALUEs to insert. ----
195 }; ----

278 bool isCalleeSaved(LocIdx L) const { 0
279 unsigned Reg = MTracker->LocIdxToLocID[L]; 0
280 if (Reg >= MTracker->NumRegs) 0
281 return false; 0
282 for (MCRegAliasIterator RAI(Reg, &TRI, true); RAI.isValid(); ++RAI) 0
283 if (CalleeSavedRegs.test(*RAI)) 0
284 return true; 0
285 return false; 0

288 // An estimate of the expected lifespan of values at a machine location, with ----
289 // a greater value corresponding to a longer expected lifespan, i.e. spill ----
290 // slots generally live longer than callee-saved registers which generally ----
291 // live longer than non-callee-saved registers. The minimum value of 0 ----
292 // corresponds to an illegal location that cannot have a "lifespan" at all. ----
293 enum class LocationQuality : unsigned char { ----
294 Illegal = 0, ----
295 Register, ----
296 CalleeSavedRegister, ----
297 SpillSlot, ----
298 Best = SpillSlot ----
299 }; ----
300 ----
301 class LocationAndQuality { ----
302 unsigned Location : 24; ----
303 unsigned Quality : 8; ----
304 ----
305 public: ----
306 LocationAndQuality() : Location(0), Quality(0) {} 0
307 LocationAndQuality(LocIdx L, LocationQuality Q) 0
308 : Location(L.asU64()), Quality(static_cast(Q)) {} 0
309 LocIdx getLoc() const { 0
310 if (!Quality) 0
311 return LocIdx::MakeIllegalLoc(); 0
312 return LocIdx(Location); 0
313 } ----
314 LocationQuality getQuality() const { return LocationQuality(Quality); } 0
315 bool isIllegal() const { return !Quality; } 0
316 bool isBest() const { return getQuality() == LocationQuality::Best; } 0
317 }; ----
318 ----
319 // Returns the LocationQuality for the location L iff the quality of L is ----
320 // is strictly greater than the provided minimum quality. ----
321 std::optional ----
322 getLocQualityIfBetter(LocIdx L, LocationQuality Min) const { 0
323 if (L.isIllegal()) 0
324 return std::nullopt; 0
325 if (Min >= LocationQuality::SpillSlot) 0
326 return std::nullopt; 0
327 if (MTracker->isSpill(L)) 0
328 return LocationQuality::SpillSlot; 0
329 if (Min >= LocationQuality::CalleeSavedRegister) 0
330 return std::nullopt; 0
331 if (isCalleeSaved(L)) 0
332 return LocationQuality::CalleeSavedRegister; 0
333 if (Min >= LocationQuality::Register) 0
334 return std::nullopt; 0
335 return LocationQuality::Register; 0
336 } ----

338 /// For a variable \p Var with the live-in value \p Value, attempts to resolve ----
339 /// the DbgValue to a concrete DBG_VALUE, emitting that value and loading the ----
340 /// tracking information to track Var throughout the block. ----
341 /// \p ValueToLoc is a map containing the best known location for every ----
342 /// ValueIDNum that Value may use. ----
343 /// \p MBB is the basic block that we are loading the live-in value for. ----
344 /// \p DbgOpStore is the map containing the DbgOpID->DbgOp mapping needed to ----
345 /// determine the values used by Value. ----
346 void loadVarInloc(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, DbgOpIDMap &DbgOpStore, 0
347 const DenseMap &ValueToLoc, ----
348 DebugVariable Var, DbgValue Value) { ----
349 SmallVector DbgOps; 0
350 SmallVector ResolvedDbgOps; 0
351 bool IsValueValid = true; 0
352 unsigned LastUseBeforeDef = 0; 0
353 ----
354 // If every value used by the incoming DbgValue is available at block ----
355 // entry, ResolvedDbgOps will contain the machine locations/constants for ----
356 // those values and will be used to emit a debug location. ----
357 // If one or more values are not yet available, but will all be defined in ----
358 // this block, then LastUseBeforeDef will track the instruction index in ----
359 // this BB at which the last of those values is defined, DbgOps will ----
360 // contain the values that we will emit when we reach that instruction. ----
361 // If one or more values are undef or not available throughout this block, ----
362 // and we can't recover as an entry value, we set IsValueValid=false and ----
363 // skip this variable. ----
364 for (DbgOpID ID : Value.getDbgOpIDs()) { 0
365 DbgOp Op = DbgOpStore.find(ID); 0
366 DbgOps.push_back(Op); 0
367 if (ID.isUndef()) { 0
368 IsValueValid = false; 0
369 break; 0
370 } ----
371 if (ID.isConst()) { 0
372 ResolvedDbgOps.push_back(Op.MO); 0
373 continue; 0
374 } ----
375 ----
376 // If the value has no location, we can't make a variable location. ----
377 const ValueIDNum &Num = Op.ID; 0
378 auto ValuesPreferredLoc = ValueToLoc.find(Num); 0
379 if (ValuesPreferredLoc->second.isIllegal()) { 0
380 // If it's a def that occurs in this block, register it as a ----
381 // use-before-def to be resolved as we step through the block. ----
382 // Continue processing values so that we add any other UseBeforeDef ----
383 // entries needed for later. ----
384 if (Num.getBlock() == (unsigned)MBB.getNumber() && !Num.isPHI()) { 0
385 LastUseBeforeDef = std::max(LastUseBeforeDef, 0
386 static_cast(Num.getInst())); 0
387 continue; 0
388 } ----
389 recoverAsEntryValue(Var, Value.Properties, Num); 0
390 IsValueValid = false; 0
391 break; 0
392 } ----
393 ----
394 // Defer modifying ActiveVLocs until after we've confirmed we have a ----
395 // live range. ----
396 LocIdx M = ValuesPreferredLoc->second.getLoc(); 0
397 ResolvedDbgOps.push_back(M); 0
398 } ----
399 ----
400 // If we cannot produce a valid value for the LiveIn value within this ----
401 // block, skip this variable. ----
402 if (!IsValueValid) 0
403 return; 0
404 ----
405 // Add UseBeforeDef entry for the last value to be defined in this block. ----
406 if (LastUseBeforeDef) { 0
407 addUseBeforeDef(Var, Value.Properties, DbgOps, 0
408 LastUseBeforeDef); ----
409 return; 0
410 } ----
411 ----
412 // The LiveIn value is available at block entry, begin tracking and record ----
413 // the transfer. ----
414 for (const ResolvedDbgOp &Op : ResolvedDbgOps) 0
415 if (!Op.IsConst) 0
416 ActiveMLocs[Op.Loc].insert(Var); 0
417 auto NewValue = ResolvedDbgValue{ResolvedDbgOps, Value.Properties}; 0
418 auto Result = ActiveVLocs.insert(std::make_pair(Var, NewValue)); 0
419 if (!Result.second) 0
420 Result.first->second = NewValue; 0
421 PendingDbgValues.push_back( 0
422 MTracker->emitLoc(ResolvedDbgOps, Var, Value.Properties)); 0
423 } 0

425 /// Load object with live-in variable values. \p mlocs contains the live-in ----
426 /// values in each machine location, while \p vlocs the live-in variable ----
427 /// values. This method picks variable locations for the live-in variables, ----
428 /// creates DBG_VALUEs and puts them in #Transfers, then prepares the other ----
429 /// object fields to track variable locations as we step through the block. ----
430 /// FIXME: could just examine mloctracker instead of passing in \p mlocs? ----
431 void ----
432 loadInlocs(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, ValueTable &MLocs, DbgOpIDMap &DbgOpStore, 0
433 const SmallVectorImpl> &VLocs, ----
434 unsigned NumLocs) { ----
435 ActiveMLocs.clear(); 0
436 ActiveVLocs.clear(); 0
437 VarLocs.clear(); 0
438 VarLocs.reserve(NumLocs); 0
439 UseBeforeDefs.clear(); 0
440 UseBeforeDefVariables.clear(); 0
441 ----
442 // Map of the preferred location for each value. ----
443 DenseMap ValueToLoc; 0
444 ----
445 // Initialized the preferred-location map with illegal locations, to be ----
446 // filled in later. ----
447 for (const auto &VLoc : VLocs) 0
448 if (VLoc.second.Kind == DbgValue::Def) 0
449 for (DbgOpID OpID : VLoc.second.getDbgOpIDs()) 0
450 if (!OpID.ID.IsConst) 0
451 ValueToLoc.insert({DbgOpStore.find(OpID).ID, LocationAndQuality()}); 0
452 ----
453 ActiveMLocs.reserve(VLocs.size()); 0
454 ActiveVLocs.reserve(VLocs.size()); 0
455 ----
456 // Produce a map of value numbers to the current machine locs they live ----
457 // in. When emulating VarLocBasedImpl, there should only be one ----
458 // location; when not, we get to pick. ----
459 for (auto Location : MTracker->locations()) { 0
460 LocIdx Idx = Location.Idx; 0
461 ValueIDNum &VNum = MLocs[Idx.asU64()]; 0
462 if (VNum == ValueIDNum::EmptyValue) 0
463 continue; 0
464 VarLocs.push_back(VNum); 0
465 ----
466 // Is there a variable that wants a location for this value? If not, skip. ----
467 auto VIt = ValueToLoc.find(VNum); 0
468 if (VIt == ValueToLoc.end()) 0
469 continue; 0
470 ----
471 auto &Previous = VIt->second; 0
472 // If this is the first location with that value, pick it. Otherwise, ----
473 // consider whether it's a "longer term" location. ----
474 std::optional ReplacementQuality = ----
475 getLocQualityIfBetter(Idx, Previous.getQuality()); 0
476 if (ReplacementQuality) 0
477 Previous = LocationAndQuality(Idx, *ReplacementQuality); 0
478 } ----
479 ----
480 // Now map variables to their picked LocIdxes. ----
481 for (const auto &Var : VLocs) { 0
482 loadVarInloc(MBB, DbgOpStore, ValueToLoc, Var.first, Var.second); 0
483 } ----
484 flushDbgValues(MBB.begin(), &MBB); 0
485 } 0

487 /// Record that \p Var has value \p ID, a value that becomes available ----
488 /// later in the function. ----
489 void addUseBeforeDef(const DebugVariable &Var, 0
490 const DbgValueProperties &Properties, ----
491 const SmallVectorImpl &DbgOps, unsigned Inst) { ----
492 UseBeforeDefs[Inst].emplace_back(DbgOps, Var, Properties); 0
493 UseBeforeDefVariables.insert(Var); 0
494 } 0
495 ----
496 /// After the instruction at index \p Inst and position \p pos has been ----
497 /// processed, check whether it defines a variable value in a use-before-def. ----
498 /// If so, and the variable value hasn't changed since the start of the ----
499 /// block, create a DBG_VALUE. ----
500 void checkInstForNewValues(unsigned Inst, MachineBasicBlock::iterator pos) { 0
501 auto MIt = UseBeforeDefs.find(Inst); 0
502 if (MIt == UseBeforeDefs.end()) 0
503 return; 0
504 ----
505 // Map of values to the locations that store them for every value used by ----
506 // the variables that may have become available. ----
507 SmallDenseMap ValueToLoc; 0
508 ----
509 // Populate ValueToLoc with illegal default mappings for every value used by ----
510 // any UseBeforeDef variables for this instruction. ----
511 for (auto &Use : MIt->second) { 0
512 if (!UseBeforeDefVariables.count(Use.Var)) 0
513 continue; 0
514 ----
515 for (DbgOp &Op : Use.Values) { 0
516 assert(!Op.isUndef() && "UseBeforeDef erroneously created for a " 0
517 "DbgValue with undef values."); ----
518 if (Op.IsConst) 0
519 continue; 0
520 ----
521 ValueToLoc.insert({Op.ID, LocationAndQuality()}); 0
522 } ----
523 } ----
524 ----
525 // Exit early if we have no DbgValues to produce. ----
526 if (ValueToLoc.empty()) 0
527 return; 0
528 ----
529 // Determine the best location for each desired value. ----
530 for (auto Location : MTracker->locations()) { 0
531 LocIdx Idx = Location.Idx; 0
532 ValueIDNum &LocValueID = Location.Value; 0
533 ----
534 // Is there a variable that wants a location for this value? If not, skip. ----
535 auto VIt = ValueToLoc.find(LocValueID); 0
536 if (VIt == ValueToLoc.end()) 0
537 continue; 0
538 ----
539 auto &Previous = VIt->second; 0
540 // If this is the first location with that value, pick it. Otherwise, ----
541 // consider whether it's a "longer term" location. ----
542 std::optional ReplacementQuality = ----
543 getLocQualityIfBetter(Idx, Previous.getQuality()); 0
544 if (ReplacementQuality) 0
545 Previous = LocationAndQuality(Idx, *ReplacementQuality); 0
546 } ----
547 ----
548 // Using the map of values to locations, produce a final set of values for ----
549 // this variable. ----
550 for (auto &Use : MIt->second) { 0
551 if (!UseBeforeDefVariables.count(Use.Var)) 0
552 continue; 0
553 ----
554 SmallVector DbgOps; 0
555 ----
556 for (DbgOp &Op : Use.Values) { 0
557 if (Op.IsConst) { 0
558 DbgOps.push_back(Op.MO); 0
559 continue; 0
560 } ----
561 LocIdx NewLoc = ValueToLoc.find(Op.ID)->second.getLoc(); 0
562 if (NewLoc.isIllegal()) 0
563 break; 0
564 DbgOps.push_back(NewLoc); 0
565 } ----
566 ----
567 // If at least one value used by this debug value is no longer available, ----
568 // i.e. one of the values was killed before we finished defining all of ----
569 // the values used by this variable, discard. ----
570 if (DbgOps.size() != Use.Values.size()) 0
571 continue; 0
572 ----
573 // Otherwise, we're good to go. ----
574 PendingDbgValues.push_back( 0
575 MTracker->emitLoc(DbgOps, Use.Var, Use.Properties)); 0
576 } 0
577 flushDbgValues(pos, nullptr); 0
578 } 0
579 ----
580 /// Helper to move created DBG_VALUEs into Transfers collection. ----
581 void flushDbgValues(MachineBasicBlock::iterator Pos, MachineBasicBlock *MBB) { 0
582 if (PendingDbgValues.size() == 0) 0
583 return; 0
584 ----
585 // Pick out the instruction start position. ----
586 MachineBasicBlock::instr_iterator BundleStart; 0
587 if (MBB && Pos == MBB->begin()) 0
588 BundleStart = MBB->instr_begin(); 0
589 else ----
590 BundleStart = getBundleStart(Pos->getIterator()); 0
591 ----
592 Transfers.push_back({BundleStart, MBB, PendingDbgValues}); 0
593 PendingDbgValues.clear(); 0
594 } ----
595 ----
596 bool isEntryValueVariable(const DebugVariable &Var, 0
597 const DIExpression *Expr) const { ----
598 if (!Var.getVariable()->isParameter()) 0
599 return false; 0
600 ----
601 if (Var.getInlinedAt()) 0
602 return false; 0
603 ----
604 if (Expr->getNumElements() > 0 && !Expr->isDeref()) 0
605 return false; 0
606 ----
607 return true; 0
608 } ----
609 ----
610 bool isEntryValueValue(const ValueIDNum &Val) const { 0
611 // Must be in entry block (block number zero), and be a PHI / live-in value. ----
612 if (Val.getBlock() || !Val.isPHI()) 0
613 return false; 0
614 ----
615 // Entry values must enter in a register. ----
616 if (MTracker->isSpill(Val.getLoc())) 0
617 return false; 0
618 ----
619 Register SP = TLI->getStackPointerRegisterToSaveRestore(); 0
620 Register FP = TRI.getFrameRegister(MF); 0
621 Register Reg = MTracker->LocIdxToLocID[Val.getLoc()]; 0
622 return Reg != SP && Reg != FP; 0
623 } ----
624 ----
625 bool recoverAsEntryValue(const DebugVariable &Var, 0
626 const DbgValueProperties &Prop, ----
627 const ValueIDNum &Num) { ----
628 // Is this variable location a candidate to be an entry value. First, ----
629 // should we be trying this at all? ----
630 if (!ShouldEmitDebugEntryValues) 0
631 return false; 0
632 ----
633 const DIExpression *DIExpr = Prop.DIExpr; 0
634 ----
635 // We don't currently emit entry values for DBG_VALUE_LISTs. ----
636 if (Prop.IsVariadic) { 0
637 // If this debug value can be converted to be non-variadic, then do so; ----
638 // otherwise give up. ----
639 auto NonVariadicExpression = ----
640 DIExpression::convertToNonVariadicExpression(DIExpr); 0
641 if (!NonVariadicExpression) 0
642 return false; 0
643 DIExpr = *NonVariadicExpression; 0
644 } ----
645 ----
646 // Is the variable appropriate for entry values (i.e., is a parameter). ----
647 if (!isEntryValueVariable(Var, DIExpr)) 0
648 return false; 0
649 ----
650 // Is the value assigned to this variable still the entry value? ----
651 if (!isEntryValueValue(Num)) 0
652 return false; 0
653 ----
654 // Emit a variable location using an entry value expression. ----
655 DIExpression *NewExpr = ----
656 DIExpression::prepend(DIExpr, DIExpression::EntryValue); 0
657 Register Reg = MTracker->LocIdxToLocID[Num.getLoc()]; 0
658 MachineOperand MO = MachineOperand::CreateReg(Reg, false); 0
659 ----
660 PendingDbgValues.push_back( 0
661 emitMOLoc(MO, Var, {NewExpr, Prop.Indirect, false})); 0
662 return true; 0
663 } ----
664 ----
665 /// Change a variable value after encountering a DBG_VALUE inside a block. ----
666 void redefVar(const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
667 DebugVariable Var(MI.getDebugVariable(), MI.getDebugExpression(), ----
668 MI.getDebugLoc()->getInlinedAt()); 0
669 DbgValueProperties Properties(MI); 0
670 ----
671 // Ignore non-register locations, we don't transfer those. ----
672 if (MI.isUndefDebugValue() || 0
673 all_of(MI.debug_operands(), 0
674 [](const MachineOperand &MO) { return !MO.isReg(); })) { 0
675 auto It = ActiveVLocs.find(Var); 0
676 if (It != ActiveVLocs.end()) { 0
677 for (LocIdx Loc : It->second.loc_indices()) 0
678 ActiveMLocs[Loc].erase(Var); 0
679 ActiveVLocs.erase(It); 0
680 } ----
681 // Any use-before-defs no longer apply. ----
682 UseBeforeDefVariables.erase(Var); 0
683 return; 0
684 } ----
685 ----
686 SmallVector NewLocs; 0
687 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.debug_operands()) { 0
688 if (MO.isReg()) { 0
689 // Any undef regs have already been filtered out above. ----
690 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
691 LocIdx NewLoc = MTracker->getRegMLoc(Reg); 0
692 NewLocs.push_back(NewLoc); 0
693 } else { ----
694 NewLocs.push_back(MO); 0
695 } ----
696 } ----
697 ----
698 redefVar(MI, Properties, NewLocs); 0
699 } 0
700 ----
701 /// Handle a change in variable location within a block. Terminate the ----
702 /// variables current location, and record the value it now refers to, so ----
703 /// that we can detect location transfers later on. ----
704 void redefVar(const MachineInstr &MI, const DbgValueProperties &Properties, 0
705 SmallVectorImpl &NewLocs) { ----
706 DebugVariable Var(MI.getDebugVariable(), MI.getDebugExpression(), ----
707 MI.getDebugLoc()->getInlinedAt()); 0
708 // Any use-before-defs no longer apply. ----
709 UseBeforeDefVariables.erase(Var); 0
710 ----
711 // Erase any previous location. ----
712 auto It = ActiveVLocs.find(Var); 0
713 if (It != ActiveVLocs.end()) { 0
714 for (LocIdx Loc : It->second.loc_indices()) 0
715 ActiveMLocs[Loc].erase(Var); 0
716 } ----
717 ----
718 // If there _is_ no new location, all we had to do was erase. ----
719 if (NewLocs.empty()) { 0
720 if (It != ActiveVLocs.end()) 0
721 ActiveVLocs.erase(It); 0
722 return; 0
723 } ----
724 ----
725 SmallVector> LostMLocs; 0
726 for (ResolvedDbgOp &Op : NewLocs) { 0
727 if (Op.IsConst) 0
728 continue; 0
729 ----
730 LocIdx NewLoc = Op.Loc; 0
731 ----
732 // Check whether our local copy of values-by-location in #VarLocs is out ----
733 // of date. Wipe old tracking data for the location if it's been clobbered ----
734 // in the meantime. ----
735 if (MTracker->readMLoc(NewLoc) != VarLocs[NewLoc.asU64()]) { 0
736 for (const auto &P : ActiveMLocs[NewLoc]) { 0
737 auto LostVLocIt = ActiveVLocs.find(P); 0
738 if (LostVLocIt != ActiveVLocs.end()) { 0
739 for (LocIdx Loc : LostVLocIt->second.loc_indices()) { 0
740 // Every active variable mapping for NewLoc will be cleared, no ----
741 // need to track individual variables. ----
742 if (Loc == NewLoc) 0
743 continue; 0
744 LostMLocs.emplace_back(Loc, P); 0
745 } ----
746 } ----
747 ActiveVLocs.erase(P); 0
748 } 0
749 for (const auto &LostMLoc : LostMLocs) 0
750 ActiveMLocs[LostMLoc.first].erase(LostMLoc.second); 0
751 LostMLocs.clear(); 0
752 It = ActiveVLocs.find(Var); 0
753 ActiveMLocs[NewLoc.asU64()].clear(); 0
754 VarLocs[NewLoc.asU64()] = MTracker->readMLoc(NewLoc); 0
755 } ----
756 ----
757 ActiveMLocs[NewLoc].insert(Var); 0
758 } ----
759 ----
760 if (It == ActiveVLocs.end()) { 0
761 ActiveVLocs.insert( 0
762 std::make_pair(Var, ResolvedDbgValue(NewLocs, Properties))); 0
763 } else { ----
764 It->second.Ops.assign(NewLocs); 0
765 It->second.Properties = Properties; 0
766 } ----
767 } 0
768 ----
769 /// Account for a location \p mloc being clobbered. Examine the variable ----
770 /// locations that will be terminated: and try to recover them by using ----
771 /// another location. Optionally, given \p MakeUndef, emit a DBG_VALUE to ----
772 /// explicitly terminate a location if it can't be recovered. ----
773 void clobberMloc(LocIdx MLoc, MachineBasicBlock::iterator Pos, 0
774 bool MakeUndef = true) { ----
775 auto ActiveMLocIt = ActiveMLocs.find(MLoc); 0
776 if (ActiveMLocIt == ActiveMLocs.end()) 0
777 return; 0
778 ----
779 // What was the old variable value? ----
780 ValueIDNum OldValue = VarLocs[MLoc.asU64()]; 0
781 clobberMloc(MLoc, OldValue, Pos, MakeUndef); 0
782 } ----
783 /// Overload that takes an explicit value \p OldValue for when the value in ----
784 /// \p MLoc has changed and the TransferTracker's locations have not been ----
785 /// updated yet. ----
786 void clobberMloc(LocIdx MLoc, ValueIDNum OldValue, 0
787 MachineBasicBlock::iterator Pos, bool MakeUndef = true) { ----
788 auto ActiveMLocIt = ActiveMLocs.find(MLoc); 0
789 if (ActiveMLocIt == ActiveMLocs.end()) 0
790 return; 0
791 ----
792 VarLocs[MLoc.asU64()] = ValueIDNum::EmptyValue; 0
793 ----
794 // Examine the remaining variable locations: if we can find the same value ----
795 // again, we can recover the location. ----
796 std::optional NewLoc; 0
797 for (auto Loc : MTracker->locations()) 0
798 if (Loc.Value == OldValue) 0
799 NewLoc = Loc.Idx; 0
800 ----
801 // If there is no location, and we weren't asked to make the variable ----
802 // explicitly undef, then stop here. ----
803 if (!NewLoc && !MakeUndef) { 0
804 // Try and recover a few more locations with entry values. ----
805 for (const auto &Var : ActiveMLocIt->second) { 0
806 auto &Prop = ActiveVLocs.find(Var)->second.Properties; 0
807 recoverAsEntryValue(Var, Prop, OldValue); 0
808 } 0
809 flushDbgValues(Pos, nullptr); 0
810 return; 0
811 } ----
812 ----
813 // Examine all the variables based on this location. ----
814 DenseSet NewMLocs; 0
815 // If no new location has been found, every variable that depends on this ----
816 // MLoc is dead, so end their existing MLoc->Var mappings as well. ----
817 SmallVector> LostMLocs; 0
818 for (const auto &Var : ActiveMLocIt->second) { 0
819 auto ActiveVLocIt = ActiveVLocs.find(Var); 0
820 // Re-state the variable location: if there's no replacement then NewLoc ----
821 // is std::nullopt and a $noreg DBG_VALUE will be created. Otherwise, a ----
822 // DBG_VALUE identifying the alternative location will be emitted. ----
823 const DbgValueProperties &Properties = ActiveVLocIt->second.Properties; 0
824 ----
825 // Produce the new list of debug ops - an empty list if no new location ----
826 // was found, or the existing list with the substitution MLoc -> NewLoc ----
827 // otherwise. ----
828 SmallVector DbgOps; 0
829 if (NewLoc) { 0
830 ResolvedDbgOp OldOp(MLoc); 0
831 ResolvedDbgOp NewOp(*NewLoc); 0
832 // Insert illegal ops to overwrite afterwards. ----
833 DbgOps.insert(DbgOps.begin(), ActiveVLocIt->second.Ops.size(), 0
834 ResolvedDbgOp(LocIdx::MakeIllegalLoc())); 0
835 replace_copy(ActiveVLocIt->second.Ops, DbgOps.begin(), OldOp, NewOp); 0
836 } ----
837 ----
838 PendingDbgValues.push_back(MTracker->emitLoc(DbgOps, Var, Properties)); 0
839 ----
840 // Update machine locations <=> variable locations maps. Defer updating ----
841 // ActiveMLocs to avoid invalidating the ActiveMLocIt iterator. ----
842 if (!NewLoc) { 0
843 for (LocIdx Loc : ActiveVLocIt->second.loc_indices()) { 0
844 if (Loc != MLoc) 0
845 LostMLocs.emplace_back(Loc, Var); 0
846 } ----
847 ActiveVLocs.erase(ActiveVLocIt); 0
848 } else { ----
849 ActiveVLocIt->second.Ops = DbgOps; 0
850 NewMLocs.insert(Var); 0
851 } ----
852 } 0
853 ----
854 // Remove variables from ActiveMLocs if they no longer use any other MLocs ----
855 // due to being killed by this clobber. ----
856 for (auto &LocVarIt : LostMLocs) { 0
857 auto LostMLocIt = ActiveMLocs.find(LocVarIt.first); 0
858 assert(LostMLocIt != ActiveMLocs.end() && 0
859 "Variable was using this MLoc, but ActiveMLocs[MLoc] has no " ----
860 "entries?"); ----
861 LostMLocIt->second.erase(LocVarIt.second); 0
862 } ----
863 ----
864 // We lazily track what locations have which values; if we've found a new ----
865 // location for the clobbered value, remember it. ----
866 if (NewLoc) 0
867 VarLocs[NewLoc->asU64()] = OldValue; 0
868 ----
869 flushDbgValues(Pos, nullptr); 0
870 ----
871 // Commit ActiveMLoc changes. ----
872 ActiveMLocIt->second.clear(); 0
873 if (!NewMLocs.empty()) 0
874 for (auto &Var : NewMLocs) 0
875 ActiveMLocs[*NewLoc].insert(Var); 0
876 } 0
877 ----
878 /// Transfer variables based on \p Src to be based on \p Dst. This handles ----
879 /// both register copies as well as spills and restores. Creates DBG_VALUEs ----
880 /// describing the movement. ----
881 void transferMlocs(LocIdx Src, LocIdx Dst, MachineBasicBlock::iterator Pos) { 0
882 // Does Src still contain the value num we expect? If not, it's been ----
883 // clobbered in the meantime, and our variable locations are stale. ----
884 if (VarLocs[Src.asU64()] != MTracker->readMLoc(Src)) 0
885 return; 0
886 ----
887 // assert(ActiveMLocs[Dst].size() == 0); ----
888 //^^^ Legitimate scenario on account of un-clobbered slot being assigned to? ----
889 ----
890 // Move set of active variables from one location to another. ----
891 auto MovingVars = ActiveMLocs[Src]; 0
892 ActiveMLocs[Dst].insert(MovingVars.begin(), MovingVars.end()); 0
893 VarLocs[Dst.asU64()] = VarLocs[Src.asU64()]; 0
894 ----
895 // For each variable based on Src; create a location at Dst. ----
896 ResolvedDbgOp SrcOp(Src); 0
897 ResolvedDbgOp DstOp(Dst); 0
898 for (const auto &Var : MovingVars) { 0
899 auto ActiveVLocIt = ActiveVLocs.find(Var); 0
900 assert(ActiveVLocIt != ActiveVLocs.end()); 0
901 ----
902 // Update all instances of Src in the variable's tracked values to Dst. ----
903 std::replace(ActiveVLocIt->second.Ops.begin(), 0
904 ActiveVLocIt->second.Ops.end(), SrcOp, DstOp); 0
905 ----
906 MachineInstr *MI = MTracker->emitLoc(ActiveVLocIt->second.Ops, Var, 0
907 ActiveVLocIt->second.Properties); 0
908 PendingDbgValues.push_back(MI); 0
909 } 0
910 ActiveMLocs[Src].clear(); 0
911 flushDbgValues(Pos, nullptr); 0
912 ----
913 // XXX XXX XXX "pretend to be old LDV" means dropping all tracking data ----
914 // about the old location. ----
915 if (EmulateOldLDV) 0
916 VarLocs[Src.asU64()] = ValueIDNum::EmptyValue; 0
917 } 0
918 ----
919 MachineInstrBuilder emitMOLoc(const MachineOperand &MO, 0
920 const DebugVariable &Var, ----
921 const DbgValueProperties &Properties) { ----
922 DebugLoc DL = DILocation::get(Var.getVariable()->getContext(), 0, 0, 0
923 Var.getVariable()->getScope(), ----
924 const_cast(Var.getInlinedAt())); 0
925 auto MIB = BuildMI(MF, DL, TII->get(TargetOpcode::DBG_VALUE)); 0
926 MIB.add(MO); 0
927 if (Properties.Indirect) 0
928 MIB.addImm(0); 0
929 else ----
930 MIB.addReg(0); 0
931 MIB.addMetadata(Var.getVariable()); 0
932 MIB.addMetadata(Properties.DIExpr); 0
933 return MIB; 0
934 } 0
935 }; ----
936 ----

939 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----

941 ValueIDNum ValueIDNum::EmptyValue = {UINT_MAX, UINT_MAX, UINT_MAX}; ----
942 ValueIDNum ValueIDNum::TombstoneValue = {UINT_MAX, UINT_MAX, UINT_MAX - 1}; ----

946 if (IsConst) { 0
947 dbgs() << MO; 0
948 } else { ----
949 dbgs() << MTrack->LocIdxToName(Loc); 0
950 } ----
951 } 0

953 if (IsConst) { 0
954 dbgs() << MO; 0
955 } else if (!isUndef()) { 0
956 dbgs() << MTrack->IDAsString(ID); 0
957 } ----
958 } 0
959 void DbgOpID::dump(const MLocTracker *MTrack, const DbgOpIDMap *OpStore) const { 0
960 if (!OpStore) { 0
961 dbgs() << "ID(" << asU32() << ")"; 0
962 } else { ----
963 OpStore->find(*this).dump(MTrack); 0
964 } ----
965 } 0
966 void DbgValue::dump(const MLocTracker *MTrack, 0
967 const DbgOpIDMap *OpStore) const { ----
968 if (Kind == NoVal) { 0
969 dbgs() << "NoVal(" << BlockNo << ")"; 0
970 } else if (Kind == VPHI || Kind == Def) { 0
971 if (Kind == VPHI) 0
972 dbgs() << "VPHI(" << BlockNo << ","; 0
973 else ----
974 dbgs() << "Def("; 0
975 for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx < getDbgOpIDs().size(); ++Idx) { 0
976 getDbgOpID(Idx).dump(MTrack, OpStore); 0
977 if (Idx != 0) 0
978 dbgs() << ","; 0
979 } ----
980 dbgs() << ")"; 0
981 } ----
982 if (Properties.Indirect) 0
983 dbgs() << " indir"; 0
984 if (Properties.DIExpr) 0
985 dbgs() << " " << *Properties.DIExpr; 0
986 } 0
987 #endif ----
988 ----
989 MLocTracker::MLocTracker(MachineFunction &MF, const TargetInstrInfo &TII, 0
990 const TargetRegisterInfo &TRI, ----
991 const TargetLowering &TLI) ----
992 : MF(MF), TII(TII), TRI(TRI), TLI(TLI), 0
993 LocIdxToIDNum(ValueIDNum::EmptyValue), LocIdxToLocID(0) { 0
994 NumRegs = TRI.getNumRegs(); 0
995 reset(); 0
996 LocIDToLocIdx.resize(NumRegs, LocIdx::MakeIllegalLoc()); 0
997 assert(NumRegs < (1u << NUM_LOC_BITS)); // Detect bit packing failure 0
998 ----
999 // Always track SP. This avoids the implicit clobbering caused by regmasks ----
1000 // from affectings its values. (LiveDebugValues disbelieves calls and ----
1001 // regmasks that claim to clobber SP). ----
1002 Register SP = TLI.getStackPointerRegisterToSaveRestore(); 0
1003 if (SP) { 0
1004 unsigned ID = getLocID(SP); 0
1005 (void)lookupOrTrackRegister(ID); 0
1006 ----
1007 for (MCRegAliasIterator RAI(SP, &TRI, true); RAI.isValid(); ++RAI) 0
1008 SPAliases.insert(*RAI); 0
1009 } ----
1010 ----
1011 // Build some common stack positions -- full registers being spilt to the ----
1012 // stack. ----
1013 StackSlotIdxes.insert({{8, 0}, 0}); 0
1014 StackSlotIdxes.insert({{16, 0}, 1}); 0
1015 StackSlotIdxes.insert({{32, 0}, 2}); 0
1016 StackSlotIdxes.insert({{64, 0}, 3}); 0
1017 StackSlotIdxes.insert({{128, 0}, 4}); 0
1018 StackSlotIdxes.insert({{256, 0}, 5}); 0
1019 StackSlotIdxes.insert({{512, 0}, 6}); 0
1020 ----
1021 // Traverse all the subregister idxes, and ensure there's an index for them. ----
1022 // Duplicates are no problem: we're interested in their position in the ----
1023 // stack slot, we don't want to type the slot. ----
1024 for (unsigned int I = 1; I < TRI.getNumSubRegIndices(); ++I) { 0
1025 unsigned Size = TRI.getSubRegIdxSize(I); 0
1026 unsigned Offs = TRI.getSubRegIdxOffset(I); 0
1027 unsigned Idx = StackSlotIdxes.size(); 0
1028 ----
1029 // Some subregs have -1, -2 and so forth fed into their fields, to mean ----
1030 // special backend things. Ignore those. ----
1031 if (Size > 60000 || Offs > 60000) 0
1032 continue; 0
1033 ----
1034 StackSlotIdxes.insert({{Size, Offs}, Idx}); 0
1035 } ----
1036 ----
1037 // There may also be strange register class sizes (think x86 fp80s). ----
1038 for (const TargetRegisterClass *RC : TRI.regclasses()) { 0
1039 unsigned Size = TRI.getRegSizeInBits(*RC); 0
1040 ----
1041 // We might see special reserved values as sizes, and classes for other ----
1042 // stuff the machine tries to model. If it's more than 512 bits, then it ----
1043 // is very unlikely to be a register than can be spilt. ----
1044 if (Size > 512) 0
1045 continue; 0
1046 ----
1047 unsigned Idx = StackSlotIdxes.size(); 0
1048 StackSlotIdxes.insert({{Size, 0}, Idx}); 0
1049 } ----
1050 ----
1051 for (auto &Idx : StackSlotIdxes) 0
1052 StackIdxesToPos[Idx.second] = Idx.first; 0
1053 ----
1054 NumSlotIdxes = StackSlotIdxes.size(); 0
1055 } 0
1056 ----
1057 LocIdx MLocTracker::trackRegister(unsigned ID) { 0
1058 assert(ID != 0); 0
1059 LocIdx NewIdx = LocIdx(LocIdxToIDNum.size()); 0
1060 LocIdxToIDNum.grow(NewIdx); 0
1061 LocIdxToLocID.grow(NewIdx); 0
1062 ----
1063 // Default: it's an mphi. ----
1064 ValueIDNum ValNum = {CurBB, 0, NewIdx}; 0
1065 // Was this reg ever touched by a regmask? ----
1066 for (const auto &MaskPair : reverse(Masks)) { 0
1067 if (MaskPair.first->clobbersPhysReg(ID)) { 0
1068 // There was an earlier def we skipped. ----
1069 ValNum = {CurBB, MaskPair.second, NewIdx}; 0
1070 break; 0
1071 } ----
1072 } ----
1073 ----
1074 LocIdxToIDNum[NewIdx] = ValNum; 0
1075 LocIdxToLocID[NewIdx] = ID; 0
1076 return NewIdx; 0
1077 } ----
1078 ----
1079 void MLocTracker::writeRegMask(const MachineOperand *MO, unsigned CurBB, 0
1080 unsigned InstID) { ----
1081 // Def any register we track have that isn't preserved. The regmask ----
1082 // terminates the liveness of a register, meaning its value can't be ----
1083 // relied upon -- we represent this by giving it a new value. ----
1084 for (auto Location : locations()) { 0
1085 unsigned ID = LocIdxToLocID[Location.Idx]; 0
1086 // Don't clobber SP, even if the mask says it's clobbered. ----
1087 if (ID < NumRegs && !SPAliases.count(ID) && MO->clobbersPhysReg(ID)) 0
1088 defReg(ID, CurBB, InstID); 0
1089 } ----
1090 Masks.push_back(std::make_pair(MO, InstID)); 0
1091 } 0
1092 ----
1093 std::optional MLocTracker::getOrTrackSpillLoc(SpillLoc L) { 0
1094 SpillLocationNo SpillID(SpillLocs.idFor(L)); 0
1095 ----
1096 if (SpillID.id() == 0) { 0
1097 // If there is no location, and we have reached the limit of how many stack ----
1098 // slots to track, then don't track this one. ----
1099 if (SpillLocs.size() >= StackWorkingSetLimit) 0
1100 return std::nullopt; 0
1101 ----
1102 // Spill location is untracked: create record for this one, and all ----
1103 // subregister slots too. ----
1104 SpillID = SpillLocationNo(SpillLocs.insert(L)); 0
1105 for (unsigned StackIdx = 0; StackIdx < NumSlotIdxes; ++StackIdx) { 0
1106 unsigned L = getSpillIDWithIdx(SpillID, StackIdx); 0
1107 LocIdx Idx = LocIdx(LocIdxToIDNum.size()); // New idx 0
1108 LocIdxToIDNum.grow(Idx); 0
1109 LocIdxToLocID.grow(Idx); 0
1110 LocIDToLocIdx.push_back(Idx); 0
1111 LocIdxToLocID[Idx] = L; 0
1112 // Initialize to PHI value; corresponds to the location's live-in value ----
1113 // during transfer function construction. ----
1114 LocIdxToIDNum[Idx] = ValueIDNum(CurBB, 0, Idx); 0
1115 } ----
1116 } ----
1117 return SpillID; 0
1118 } ----
1119 ----
1120 std::string MLocTracker::LocIdxToName(LocIdx Idx) const { 0
1121 unsigned ID = LocIdxToLocID[Idx]; 0
1122 if (ID >= NumRegs) { 0
1123 StackSlotPos Pos = locIDToSpillIdx(ID); 0
1124 ID -= NumRegs; 0
1125 unsigned Slot = ID / NumSlotIdxes; 0
1126 return Twine("slot ") 0
1127 .concat(Twine(Slot).concat(Twine(" sz ").concat(Twine(Pos.first) 0
1128 .concat(Twine(" offs ").concat(Twine(Pos.second)))))) 0
1129 .str(); 0
1130 } else { ----
1131 return TRI.getRegAsmName(ID).str(); 0
1132 } ----
1133 } ----
1134 ----
1135 std::string MLocTracker::IDAsString(const ValueIDNum &Num) const { 0
1136 std::string DefName = LocIdxToName(Num.getLoc()); 0
1137 return Num.asString(DefName); 0
1138 } 0

1140 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
1141 LLVM_DUMP_METHOD void MLocTracker::dump() { 0
1142 for (auto Location : locations()) { 0
1143 std::string MLocName = LocIdxToName(Location.Value.getLoc()); 0
1144 std::string DefName = Location.Value.asString(MLocName); 0
1145 dbgs() << LocIdxToName(Location.Idx) << " --> " << DefName << "\n"; 0
1146 } 0
1147 } 0
1148 ----
1149 LLVM_DUMP_METHOD void MLocTracker::dump_mloc_map() { 0
1150 for (auto Location : locations()) { 0
1151 std::string foo = LocIdxToName(Location.Idx); 0
1152 dbgs() << "Idx " << Location.Idx.asU64() << " " << foo << "\n"; 0
1153 } 0
1154 } 0
1155 #endif ----
1156 ----
1157 MachineInstrBuilder ----
1158 MLocTracker::emitLoc(const SmallVectorImpl &DbgOps, 0
1159 const DebugVariable &Var, ----
1160 const DbgValueProperties &Properties) { ----
1161 DebugLoc DL = DILocation::get(Var.getVariable()->getContext(), 0, 0, 0
1162 Var.getVariable()->getScope(), ----
1163 const_cast(Var.getInlinedAt())); 0
1164 ----
1165 const MCInstrDesc &Desc = Properties.IsVariadic 0
1166 ? TII.get(TargetOpcode::DBG_VALUE_LIST) 0
1167 : TII.get(TargetOpcode::DBG_VALUE); 0
1168 ----
1169 #ifdef EXPENSIVE_CHECKS ----
1170 assert(all_of(DbgOps, ----
1171 [](const ResolvedDbgOp &Op) { ----
1172 return Op.IsConst || !Op.Loc.isIllegal(); ----
1173 }) && ----
1174 "Did not expect illegal ops in DbgOps."); ----
1175 assert((DbgOps.size() == 0 || ----
1176 DbgOps.size() == Properties.getLocationOpCount()) && ----
1177 "Expected to have either one DbgOp per MI LocationOp, or none."); ----
1178 #endif ----
1179 ----
1180 auto GetRegOp = [](unsigned Reg) -> MachineOperand { 0
1181 return MachineOperand::CreateReg( 0
1182 /* Reg */ Reg, /* isDef */ false, /* isImp */ false, ----
1183 /* isKill */ false, /* isDead */ false, ----
1184 /* isUndef */ false, /* isEarlyClobber */ false, ----
1185 /* SubReg */ 0, /* isDebug */ true); 0
1186 }; ----
1187 ----
1188 SmallVector MOs; 0
1189 ----
1190 auto EmitUndef = [&]() { 0
1191 MOs.clear(); 0
1192 MOs.assign(Properties.getLocationOpCount(), GetRegOp(0)); 0
1193 return BuildMI(MF, DL, Desc, false, MOs, Var.getVariable(), 0
1194 Properties.DIExpr); 0
1195 }; 0
1196 ----
1197 // Don't bother passing any real operands to BuildMI if any of them would be ----
1198 // $noreg. ----
1199 if (DbgOps.empty()) 0
1200 return EmitUndef(); 0
1201 ----
1202 bool Indirect = Properties.Indirect; 0
1203 ----
1204 const DIExpression *Expr = Properties.DIExpr; 0
1205 ----
1206 assert(DbgOps.size() == Properties.getLocationOpCount()); 0
1207 ----
1208 // If all locations are valid, accumulate them into our list of ----
1209 // MachineOperands. For any spilled locations, either update the indirectness ----
1210 // register or apply the appropriate transformations in the DIExpression. ----
1211 for (size_t Idx = 0; Idx < Properties.getLocationOpCount(); ++Idx) { 0
1212 const ResolvedDbgOp &Op = DbgOps[Idx]; 0
1213 ----
1214 if (Op.IsConst) { 0
1215 MOs.push_back(Op.MO); 0
1216 continue; 0
1217 } ----
1218 ----
1219 LocIdx MLoc = Op.Loc; 0
1220 unsigned LocID = LocIdxToLocID[MLoc]; 0
1221 if (LocID >= NumRegs) { 0
1222 SpillLocationNo SpillID = locIDToSpill(LocID); 0
1223 StackSlotPos StackIdx = locIDToSpillIdx(LocID); 0
1224 unsigned short Offset = StackIdx.second; 0
1225 ----
1226 // TODO: support variables that are located in spill slots, with non-zero ----
1227 // offsets from the start of the spill slot. It would require some more ----
1228 // complex DIExpression calculations. This doesn't seem to be produced by ----
1229 // LLVM right now, so don't try and support it. ----
1230 // Accept no-subregister slots and subregisters where the offset is zero. ----
1231 // The consumer should already have type information to work out how large ----
1232 // the variable is. ----
1233 if (Offset == 0) { 0
1234 const SpillLoc &Spill = SpillLocs[SpillID.id()]; 0
1235 unsigned Base = Spill.SpillBase; 0
1236 ----
1237 // There are several ways we can dereference things, and several inputs ----
1238 // to consider: ----
1239 // * NRVO variables will appear with IsIndirect set, but should have ----
1240 // nothing else in their DIExpressions, ----
1241 // * Variables with DW_OP_stack_value in their expr already need an ----
1242 // explicit dereference of the stack location, ----
1243 // * Values that don't match the variable size need DW_OP_deref_size, ----
1244 // * Everything else can just become a simple location expression. ----
1245 ----
1246 // We need to use deref_size whenever there's a mismatch between the ----
1247 // size of value and the size of variable portion being read. ----
1248 // Additionally, we should use it whenever dealing with stack_value ----
1249 // fragments, to avoid the consumer having to determine the deref size ----
1250 // from DW_OP_piece. ----
1251 bool UseDerefSize = false; 0
1252 unsigned ValueSizeInBits = getLocSizeInBits(MLoc); 0
1253 unsigned DerefSizeInBytes = ValueSizeInBits / 8; 0
1254 if (auto Fragment = Var.getFragment()) { 0
1255 unsigned VariableSizeInBits = Fragment->SizeInBits; 0
1256 if (VariableSizeInBits != ValueSizeInBits || Expr->isComplex()) 0
1257 UseDerefSize = true; 0
1258 } else if (auto Size = Var.getVariable()->getSizeInBits()) { 0
1259 if (*Size != ValueSizeInBits) { 0
1260 UseDerefSize = true; 0
1261 } ----
1262 } ----
1263 ----
1264 SmallVector OffsetOps; 0
1265 TRI.getOffsetOpcodes(Spill.SpillOffset, OffsetOps); 0
1266 bool StackValue = false; 0
1267 ----
1268 if (Properties.Indirect) { 0
1269 // This is something like an NRVO variable, where the pointer has been ----
1270 // spilt to the stack. It should end up being a memory location, with ----
1271 // the pointer to the variable loaded off the stack with a deref: ----
1272 assert(!Expr->isImplicit()); 0
1273 OffsetOps.push_back(dwarf::DW_OP_deref); 0
1274 } else if (UseDerefSize && Expr->isSingleLocationExpression()) { 0
1275 // TODO: Figure out how to handle deref size issues for variadic ----
1276 // values. ----
1277 // We're loading a value off the stack that's not the same size as the ----
1278 // variable. Add / subtract stack offset, explicitly deref with a ----
1279 // size, and add DW_OP_stack_value if not already present. ----
1280 OffsetOps.push_back(dwarf::DW_OP_deref_size); 0
1281 OffsetOps.push_back(DerefSizeInBytes); 0
1282 StackValue = true; 0
1283 } else if (Expr->isComplex() || Properties.IsVariadic) { 0
1284 // A variable with no size ambiguity, but with extra elements in it's ----
1285 // expression. Manually dereference the stack location. ----
1286 OffsetOps.push_back(dwarf::DW_OP_deref); 0
1287 } else { ----
1288 // A plain value that has been spilt to the stack, with no further ----
1289 // context. Request a location expression, marking the DBG_VALUE as ----
1290 // IsIndirect. ----
1291 Indirect = true; 0
1292 } ----
1293 ----
1294 Expr = DIExpression::appendOpsToArg(Expr, OffsetOps, Idx, StackValue); 0
1295 MOs.push_back(GetRegOp(Base)); 0
1296 } else { 0
1297 // This is a stack location with a weird subregister offset: emit an ----
1298 // undef DBG_VALUE instead. ----
1299 return EmitUndef(); 0
1300 } ----
1301 } else { ----
1302 // Non-empty, non-stack slot, must be a plain register. ----
1303 MOs.push_back(GetRegOp(LocID)); 0
1304 } ----
1305 } ----
1306 ----
1307 return BuildMI(MF, DL, Desc, Indirect, MOs, Var.getVariable(), Expr); 0
1308 } 0
1309 ----
1310 /// Default construct and initialize the pass. ----
1311 InstrRefBasedLDV::InstrRefBasedLDV() = default; 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1312 ----
1313 bool InstrRefBasedLDV::isCalleeSaved(LocIdx L) const { 0
1314 unsigned Reg = MTracker->LocIdxToLocID[L]; 0
1315 return isCalleeSavedReg(Reg); 0
1316 } ----
1317 bool InstrRefBasedLDV::isCalleeSavedReg(Register R) const { 0
1318 for (MCRegAliasIterator RAI(R, TRI, true); RAI.isValid(); ++RAI) 0
1319 if (CalleeSavedRegs.test(*RAI)) 0
1320 return true; 0
1321 return false; 0
1322 } ----

1326 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----

1332 ----
1333 std::optional ----
1334 InstrRefBasedLDV::extractSpillBaseRegAndOffset(const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1335 assert(MI.hasOneMemOperand() && 0
1336 "Spill instruction does not have exactly one memory operand?"); ----
1337 auto MMOI = MI.memoperands_begin(); 0
1338 const PseudoSourceValue *PVal = (*MMOI)->getPseudoValue(); 0
1339 assert(PVal->kind() == PseudoSourceValue::FixedStack && 0
1340 "Inconsistent memory operand in spill instruction"); ----
1341 int FI = cast(PVal)->getFrameIndex(); 0
1342 const MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MI.getParent(); 0
1343 Register Reg; 0
1344 StackOffset Offset = TFI->getFrameIndexReference(*MBB->getParent(), FI, Reg); 0
1345 return MTracker->getOrTrackSpillLoc({Reg, Offset}); 0
1346 } ----
1347 ----
1348 std::optional ----
1349 InstrRefBasedLDV::findLocationForMemOperand(const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1350 std::optional SpillLoc = extractSpillBaseRegAndOffset(MI); 0
1351 if (!SpillLoc) 0
1352 return std::nullopt; 0
1353 ----
1354 // Where in the stack slot is this value defined -- i.e., what size of value ----
1355 // is this? An important question, because it could be loaded into a register ----
1356 // from the stack at some point. Happily the memory operand will tell us ----
1357 // the size written to the stack. ----
1358 auto *MemOperand = *MI.memoperands_begin(); 0
1359 unsigned SizeInBits = MemOperand->getSizeInBits(); 0
1360 ----
1361 // Find that position in the stack indexes we're tracking. ----
1362 auto IdxIt = MTracker->StackSlotIdxes.find({SizeInBits, 0}); 0
1363 if (IdxIt == MTracker->StackSlotIdxes.end()) 0
1364 // That index is not tracked. This is suprising, and unlikely to ever ----
1365 // occur, but the safe action is to indicate the variable is optimised out. ----
1366 return std::nullopt; 0
1367 ----
1368 unsigned SpillID = MTracker->getSpillIDWithIdx(*SpillLoc, IdxIt->second); 0
1369 return MTracker->getSpillMLoc(SpillID); 0
1370 } ----
1371 ----
1372 /// End all previous ranges related to @MI and start a new range from @MI ----
1373 /// if it is a DBG_VALUE instr. ----
1374 bool InstrRefBasedLDV::transferDebugValue(const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1375 if (!MI.isDebugValue()) 0
1376 return false; 0
1377 ----
1378 const DILocalVariable *Var = MI.getDebugVariable(); 0
1379 const DIExpression *Expr = MI.getDebugExpression(); 0
1380 const DILocation *DebugLoc = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
1381 const DILocation *InlinedAt = DebugLoc->getInlinedAt(); 0
1382 assert(Var->isValidLocationForIntrinsic(DebugLoc) && 0
1383 "Expected inlined-at fields to agree"); ----
1384 ----
1385 DebugVariable V(Var, Expr, InlinedAt); 0
1386 DbgValueProperties Properties(MI); 0
1387 ----
1388 // If there are no instructions in this lexical scope, do no location tracking ----
1389 // at all, this variable shouldn't get a legitimate location range. ----
1390 auto *Scope = LS.findLexicalScope(MI.getDebugLoc().get()); 0
1391 if (Scope == nullptr) 0
1392 return true; // handled it; by doing nothing 0
1393 ----
1394 // MLocTracker needs to know that this register is read, even if it's only ----
1395 // read by a debug inst. ----
1396 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.debug_operands()) 0
1397 if (MO.isReg() && MO.getReg() != 0) 0
1398 (void)MTracker->readReg(MO.getReg()); 0
1399 ----
1400 // If we're preparing for the second analysis (variables), the machine value ----
1401 // locations are already solved, and we report this DBG_VALUE and the value ----
1402 // it refers to to VLocTracker. ----
1403 if (VTracker) { 0
1404 SmallVector DebugOps; 0
1405 // Feed defVar the new variable location, or if this is a DBG_VALUE $noreg, ----
1406 // feed defVar None. ----
1407 if (!MI.isUndefDebugValue()) { 0
1408 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.debug_operands()) { 0
1409 // There should be no undef registers here, as we've screened for undef ----
1410 // debug values. ----
1411 if (MO.isReg()) { 0
1412 DebugOps.push_back(DbgOpStore.insert(MTracker->readReg(MO.getReg()))); 0
1413 } else if (MO.isImm() || MO.isFPImm() || MO.isCImm()) { 0
1414 DebugOps.push_back(DbgOpStore.insert(MO)); 0
1415 } else { ----
1416 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected debug operand type."); 0
1417 } ----
1418 } ----
1419 } ----
1420 VTracker->defVar(MI, Properties, DebugOps); 0
1421 } 0
1422 ----
1423 // If performing final tracking of transfers, report this variable definition ----
1424 // to the TransferTracker too. ----
1425 if (TTracker) 0
1426 TTracker->redefVar(MI); 0
1427 return true; 0
1428 } ----
1429 ----
1430 std::optional InstrRefBasedLDV::getValueForInstrRef( 0
1431 unsigned InstNo, unsigned OpNo, MachineInstr &MI, ----
1432 const ValueTable *MLiveOuts, const ValueTable *MLiveIns) { ----
1433 // Various optimizations may have happened to the value during codegen, ----
1434 // recorded in the value substitution table. Apply any substitutions to ----
1435 // the instruction / operand number in this DBG_INSTR_REF, and collect ----
1436 // any subregister extractions performed during optimization. ----
1437 const MachineFunction &MF = *MI.getParent()->getParent(); 0
1438 ----
1439 // Create dummy substitution with Src set, for lookup. ----
1440 auto SoughtSub = ----
1441 MachineFunction::DebugSubstitution({InstNo, OpNo}, {0, 0}, 0); 0
1442 ----
1443 SmallVector SeenSubregs; 0
1444 auto LowerBoundIt = llvm::lower_bound(MF.DebugValueSubstitutions, SoughtSub); 0
1445 while (LowerBoundIt != MF.DebugValueSubstitutions.end() && 0
1446 LowerBoundIt->Src == SoughtSub.Src) { 0
1447 std::tie(InstNo, OpNo) = LowerBoundIt->Dest; 0
1448 SoughtSub.Src = LowerBoundIt->Dest; 0
1449 if (unsigned Subreg = LowerBoundIt->Subreg) 0
1450 SeenSubregs.push_back(Subreg); 0
1451 LowerBoundIt = llvm::lower_bound(MF.DebugValueSubstitutions, SoughtSub); 0
1452 } ----
1453 ----
1454 // Default machine value number is -- if no instruction defines ----
1455 // the corresponding value, it must have been optimized out. ----
1456 std::optional NewID; 0
1457 ----
1458 // Try to lookup the instruction number, and find the machine value number ----
1459 // that it defines. It could be an instruction, or a PHI. ----
1460 auto InstrIt = DebugInstrNumToInstr.find(InstNo); 0
1461 auto PHIIt = llvm::lower_bound(DebugPHINumToValue, InstNo); 0
1462 if (InstrIt != DebugInstrNumToInstr.end()) { 0
1463 const MachineInstr &TargetInstr = *InstrIt->second.first; 0
1464 uint64_t BlockNo = TargetInstr.getParent()->getNumber(); 0
1465 ----
1466 // Pick out the designated operand. It might be a memory reference, if ----
1467 // a register def was folded into a stack store. ----
1468 if (OpNo == MachineFunction::DebugOperandMemNumber && 0
1469 TargetInstr.hasOneMemOperand()) { 0
1470 std::optional L = findLocationForMemOperand(TargetInstr); 0
1471 if (L) 0
1472 NewID = ValueIDNum(BlockNo, InstrIt->second.second, *L); 0
1473 } else if (OpNo != MachineFunction::DebugOperandMemNumber) { 0
1474 // Permit the debug-info to be completely wrong: identifying a nonexistant ----
1475 // operand, or one that is not a register definition, means something ----
1476 // unexpected happened during optimisation. Broken debug-info, however, ----
1477 // shouldn't crash the compiler -- instead leave the variable value as ----
1478 // None, which will make it appear "optimised out". ----
1479 if (OpNo < TargetInstr.getNumOperands()) { 0
1480 const MachineOperand &MO = TargetInstr.getOperand(OpNo); 0
1481 ----
1482 if (MO.isReg() && MO.isDef() && MO.getReg()) { 0
1483 unsigned LocID = MTracker->getLocID(MO.getReg()); 0
1484 LocIdx L = MTracker->LocIDToLocIdx[LocID]; 0
1485 NewID = ValueIDNum(BlockNo, InstrIt->second.second, L); 0
1486 } ----
1487 } ----
1488 ----
1489 if (!NewID) { 0
1490 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1491 { dbgs() << "Seen instruction reference to illegal operand\n"; }); ----
1492 } ----
1493 } ----
1494 // else: NewID is left as None. ----
1495 } else if (PHIIt != DebugPHINumToValue.end() && PHIIt->InstrNum == InstNo) { 0
1496 // It's actually a PHI value. Which value it is might not be obvious, use ----
1497 // the resolver helper to find out. ----
1498 NewID = resolveDbgPHIs(*MI.getParent()->getParent(), MLiveOuts, MLiveIns, 0
1499 MI, InstNo); ----
1500 } ----
1501 ----
1502 // Apply any subregister extractions, in reverse. We might have seen code ----
1503 // like this: ----
1504 // CALL64 @foo, implicit-def $rax ----
1505 // %0:gr64 = COPY $rax ----
1506 // %1:gr32 = COPY %0.sub_32bit ----
1507 // %2:gr16 = COPY %1.sub_16bit ----
1508 // %3:gr8 = COPY %2.sub_8bit ----
1509 // In which case each copy would have been recorded as a substitution with ----
1510 // a subregister qualifier. Apply those qualifiers now. ----
1511 if (NewID && !SeenSubregs.empty()) { 0
1512 unsigned Offset = 0; 0
1513 unsigned Size = 0; 0
1514 ----
1515 // Look at each subregister that we passed through, and progressively ----
1516 // narrow in, accumulating any offsets that occur. Substitutions should ----
1517 // only ever be the same or narrower width than what they read from; ----
1518 // iterate in reverse order so that we go from wide to small. ----
1519 for (unsigned Subreg : reverse(SeenSubregs)) { 0
1520 unsigned ThisSize = TRI->getSubRegIdxSize(Subreg); 0
1521 unsigned ThisOffset = TRI->getSubRegIdxOffset(Subreg); 0
1522 Offset += ThisOffset; 0
1523 Size = (Size == 0) ? ThisSize : std::min(Size, ThisSize); 0
1524 } ----
1525 ----
1526 // If that worked, look for an appropriate subregister with the register ----
1527 // where the define happens. Don't look at values that were defined during ----
1528 // a stack write: we can't currently express register locations within ----
1529 // spills. ----
1530 LocIdx L = NewID->getLoc(); 0
1531 if (NewID && !MTracker->isSpill(L)) { 0
1532 // Find the register class for the register where this def happened. ----
1533 // FIXME: no index for this? ----
1534 Register Reg = MTracker->LocIdxToLocID[L]; 0
1535 const TargetRegisterClass *TRC = nullptr; 0
1536 for (const auto *TRCI : TRI->regclasses()) 0
1537 if (TRCI->contains(Reg)) 0
1538 TRC = TRCI; 0
1539 assert(TRC && "Couldn't find target register class?"); 0
1540 ----
1541 // If the register we have isn't the right size or in the right place, ----
1542 // Try to find a subregister inside it. ----
1543 unsigned MainRegSize = TRI->getRegSizeInBits(*TRC); 0
1544 if (Size != MainRegSize || Offset) { 0
1545 // Enumerate all subregisters, searching. ----
1546 Register NewReg = 0; 0
1547 for (MCPhysReg SR : TRI->subregs(Reg)) { 0
1548 unsigned Subreg = TRI->getSubRegIndex(Reg, SR); 0
1549 unsigned SubregSize = TRI->getSubRegIdxSize(Subreg); 0
1550 unsigned SubregOffset = TRI->getSubRegIdxOffset(Subreg); 0
1551 if (SubregSize == Size && SubregOffset == Offset) { 0
1552 NewReg = SR; 0
1553 break; 0
1554 } ----
1555 } ----
1556 ----
1557 // If we didn't find anything: there's no way to express our value. ----
1558 if (!NewReg) { 0
1559 NewID = std::nullopt; 0
1560 } else { ----
1561 // Re-state the value as being defined within the subregister ----
1562 // that we found. ----
1563 LocIdx NewLoc = MTracker->lookupOrTrackRegister(NewReg); 0
1564 NewID = ValueIDNum(NewID->getBlock(), NewID->getInst(), NewLoc); 0
1565 } ----
1566 } ----
1567 } else { ----
1568 // If we can't handle subregisters, unset the new value. ----
1569 NewID = std::nullopt; 0
1570 } ----
1571 } ----
1572 ----
1573 return NewID; 0
1574 } 0
1575 ----
1576 bool InstrRefBasedLDV::transferDebugInstrRef(MachineInstr &MI, 0
1577 const ValueTable *MLiveOuts, ----
1578 const ValueTable *MLiveIns) { ----
1579 if (!MI.isDebugRef()) 0
1580 return false; 0
1581 ----
1582 // Only handle this instruction when we are building the variable value ----
1583 // transfer function. ----
1584 if (!VTracker && !TTracker) 0
1585 return false; 0
1586 ----
1587 const DILocalVariable *Var = MI.getDebugVariable(); 0
1588 const DIExpression *Expr = MI.getDebugExpression(); 0
1589 const DILocation *DebugLoc = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
1590 const DILocation *InlinedAt = DebugLoc->getInlinedAt(); 0
1591 assert(Var->isValidLocationForIntrinsic(DebugLoc) && 0
1592 "Expected inlined-at fields to agree"); ----
1593 ----
1594 DebugVariable V(Var, Expr, InlinedAt); 0
1595 ----
1596 auto *Scope = LS.findLexicalScope(MI.getDebugLoc().get()); 0
1597 if (Scope == nullptr) 0
1598 return true; // Handled by doing nothing. This variable is never in scope. 0
1599 ----
1600 SmallVector DbgOpIDs; 0
1601 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.debug_operands()) { 0
1602 if (!MO.isDbgInstrRef()) { 0
1603 assert(!MO.isReg() && "DBG_INSTR_REF should not contain registers"); 0
1604 DbgOpID ConstOpID = DbgOpStore.insert(DbgOp(MO)); 0
1605 DbgOpIDs.push_back(ConstOpID); 0
1606 continue; 0
1607 } 0
1608 ----
1609 unsigned InstNo = MO.getInstrRefInstrIndex(); 0
1610 unsigned OpNo = MO.getInstrRefOpIndex(); 0
1611 ----
1612 // Default machine value number is -- if no instruction defines ----
1613 // the corresponding value, it must have been optimized out. ----
1614 std::optional NewID = ----
1615 getValueForInstrRef(InstNo, OpNo, MI, MLiveOuts, MLiveIns); 0
1616 // We have a value number or std::nullopt. If the latter, then kill the ----
1617 // entire debug value. ----
1618 if (NewID) { 0
1619 DbgOpIDs.push_back(DbgOpStore.insert(*NewID)); 0
1620 } else { ----
1621 DbgOpIDs.clear(); 0
1622 break; 0
1623 } ----
1624 } ----
1625 ----
1626 // We have a DbgOpID for every value or for none. Tell the variable value ----
1627 // tracker about it. The rest of this LiveDebugValues implementation acts ----
1628 // exactly the same for DBG_INSTR_REFs as DBG_VALUEs (just, the former can ----
1629 // refer to values that aren't immediately available). ----
1630 DbgValueProperties Properties(Expr, false, true); 0
1631 if (VTracker) 0
1632 VTracker->defVar(MI, Properties, DbgOpIDs); 0
1633 ----
1634 // If we're on the final pass through the function, decompose this INSTR_REF ----
1635 // into a plain DBG_VALUE. ----
1636 if (!TTracker) 0
1637 return true; 0
1638 ----
1639 // Fetch the concrete DbgOps now, as we will need them later. ----
1640 SmallVector DbgOps; 0
1641 for (DbgOpID OpID : DbgOpIDs) { 0
1642 DbgOps.push_back(DbgOpStore.find(OpID)); 0
1643 } ----
1644 ----
1645 // Pick a location for the machine value number, if such a location exists. ----
1646 // (This information could be stored in TransferTracker to make it faster). ----
1647 SmallDenseMap FoundLocs; 0
1648 SmallVector ValuesToFind; 0
1649 // Initialized the preferred-location map with illegal locations, to be ----
1650 // filled in later. ----
1651 for (const DbgOp &Op : DbgOps) { 0
1652 if (!Op.IsConst) 0
1653 if (FoundLocs.insert({Op.ID, TransferTracker::LocationAndQuality()}) 0
1654 .second) 0
1655 ValuesToFind.push_back(Op.ID); 0
1656 } ----
1657 ----
1658 for (auto Location : MTracker->locations()) { 0
1659 LocIdx CurL = Location.Idx; 0
1660 ValueIDNum ID = MTracker->readMLoc(CurL); 0
1661 auto ValueToFindIt = find(ValuesToFind, ID); 0
1662 if (ValueToFindIt == ValuesToFind.end()) 0
1663 continue; 0
1664 auto &Previous = FoundLocs.find(ID)->second; 0
1665 // If this is the first location with that value, pick it. Otherwise, ----
1666 // consider whether it's a "longer term" location. ----
1667 std::optional ReplacementQuality = ----
1668 TTracker->getLocQualityIfBetter(CurL, Previous.getQuality()); 0
1669 if (ReplacementQuality) { 0
1670 Previous = TransferTracker::LocationAndQuality(CurL, *ReplacementQuality); 0
1671 if (Previous.isBest()) { 0
1672 ValuesToFind.erase(ValueToFindIt); 0
1673 if (ValuesToFind.empty()) 0
1674 break; 0
1675 } ----
1676 } ----
1677 } ----
1678 ----
1679 SmallVector NewLocs; 0
1680 for (const DbgOp &DbgOp : DbgOps) { 0
1681 if (DbgOp.IsConst) { 0
1682 NewLocs.push_back(DbgOp.MO); 0
1683 continue; 0
1684 } ----
1685 LocIdx FoundLoc = FoundLocs.find(DbgOp.ID)->second.getLoc(); 0
1686 if (FoundLoc.isIllegal()) { 0
1687 NewLocs.clear(); 0
1688 break; 0
1689 } ----
1690 NewLocs.push_back(FoundLoc); 0
1691 } ----
1692 // Tell transfer tracker that the variable value has changed. ----
1693 TTracker->redefVar(MI, Properties, NewLocs); 0
1694 ----
1695 // If there were values with no location, but all such values are defined in ----
1696 // later instructions in this block, this is a block-local use-before-def. ----
1697 if (!DbgOps.empty() && NewLocs.empty()) { 0
1698 bool IsValidUseBeforeDef = true; 0
1699 uint64_t LastUseBeforeDef = 0; 0
1700 for (auto ValueLoc : FoundLocs) { 0
1701 ValueIDNum NewID = ValueLoc.first; 0
1702 LocIdx FoundLoc = ValueLoc.second.getLoc(); 0
1703 if (!FoundLoc.isIllegal()) 0
1704 continue; 0
1705 // If we have an value with no location that is not defined in this block, ----
1706 // then it has no location in this block, leaving this value undefined. ----
1707 if (NewID.getBlock() != CurBB || NewID.getInst() <= CurInst) { 0
1708 IsValidUseBeforeDef = false; 0
1709 break; 0
1710 } ----
1711 LastUseBeforeDef = std::max(LastUseBeforeDef, NewID.getInst()); 0
1712 } ----
1713 if (IsValidUseBeforeDef) { 0
1714 TTracker->addUseBeforeDef(V, {MI.getDebugExpression(), false, true}, 0
1715 DbgOps, LastUseBeforeDef); ----
1716 } ----
1717 } ----
1718 ----
1719 // Produce a DBG_VALUE representing what this DBG_INSTR_REF meant. ----
1720 // This DBG_VALUE is potentially a $noreg / undefined location, if ----
1721 // FoundLoc is illegal. ----
1722 // (XXX -- could morph the DBG_INSTR_REF in the future). ----
1723 MachineInstr *DbgMI = MTracker->emitLoc(NewLocs, V, Properties); 0
1724 ----
1725 TTracker->PendingDbgValues.push_back(DbgMI); 0
1726 TTracker->flushDbgValues(MI.getIterator(), nullptr); 0
1727 return true; 0
1728 } 0
1729 ----
1730 bool InstrRefBasedLDV::transferDebugPHI(MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1731 if (!MI.isDebugPHI()) 0
1732 return false; 0
1733 ----
1734 // Analyse these only when solving the machine value location problem. ----
1735 if (VTracker || TTracker) 0
1736 return true; 0
1737 ----
1738 // First operand is the value location, either a stack slot or register. ----
1739 // Second is the debug instruction number of the original PHI. ----
1740 const MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(0); 0
1741 unsigned InstrNum = MI.getOperand(1).getImm(); 0
1742 ----
1743 auto EmitBadPHI = [this, &MI, InstrNum]() -> bool { 0
1744 // Helper lambda to do any accounting when we fail to find a location for ----
1745 // a DBG_PHI. This can happen if DBG_PHIs are malformed, or refer to a ----
1746 // dead stack slot, for example. ----
1747 // Record a DebugPHIRecord with an empty value + location. ----
1748 DebugPHINumToValue.push_back( 0
1749 {InstrNum, MI.getParent(), std::nullopt, std::nullopt}); 0
1750 return true; 0
1751 }; 0
1752 ----
1753 if (MO.isReg() && MO.getReg()) { 0
1754 // The value is whatever's currently in the register. Read and record it, ----
1755 // to be analysed later. ----
1756 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1757 ValueIDNum Num = MTracker->readReg(Reg); 0
1758 auto PHIRec = DebugPHIRecord( ----
1759 {InstrNum, MI.getParent(), Num, MTracker->lookupOrTrackRegister(Reg)}); 0
1760 DebugPHINumToValue.push_back(PHIRec); 0
1761 ----
1762 // Ensure this register is tracked. ----
1763 for (MCRegAliasIterator RAI(MO.getReg(), TRI, true); RAI.isValid(); ++RAI) 0
1764 MTracker->lookupOrTrackRegister(*RAI); 0
1765 } else if (MO.isFI()) { 0
1766 // The value is whatever's in this stack slot. ----
1767 unsigned FI = MO.getIndex(); 0
1768 ----
1769 // If the stack slot is dead, then this was optimized away. ----
1770 // FIXME: stack slot colouring should account for slots that get merged. ----
1771 if (MFI->isDeadObjectIndex(FI)) 0
1772 return EmitBadPHI(); 0
1773 ----
1774 // Identify this spill slot, ensure it's tracked. ----
1775 Register Base; 0
1776 StackOffset Offs = TFI->getFrameIndexReference(*MI.getMF(), FI, Base); 0
1777 SpillLoc SL = {Base, Offs}; 0
1778 std::optional SpillNo = MTracker->getOrTrackSpillLoc(SL); 0
1779 ----
1780 // We might be able to find a value, but have chosen not to, to avoid ----
1781 // tracking too much stack information. ----
1782 if (!SpillNo) 0
1783 return EmitBadPHI(); 0
1784 ----
1785 // Any stack location DBG_PHI should have an associate bit-size. ----
1786 assert(MI.getNumOperands() == 3 && "Stack DBG_PHI with no size?"); 0
1787 unsigned slotBitSize = MI.getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1788 ----
1789 unsigned SpillID = MTracker->getLocID(*SpillNo, {slotBitSize, 0}); 0
1790 LocIdx SpillLoc = MTracker->getSpillMLoc(SpillID); 0
1791 ValueIDNum Result = MTracker->readMLoc(SpillLoc); 0
1792 ----
1793 // Record this DBG_PHI for later analysis. ----
1794 auto DbgPHI = DebugPHIRecord({InstrNum, MI.getParent(), Result, SpillLoc}); 0
1795 DebugPHINumToValue.push_back(DbgPHI); 0
1796 } else { ----
1797 // Else: if the operand is neither a legal register or a stack slot, then ----
1798 // we're being fed illegal debug-info. Record an empty PHI, so that any ----
1799 // debug users trying to read this number will be put off trying to ----
1800 // interpret the value. ----
1801 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1802 { dbgs() << "Seen DBG_PHI with unrecognised operand format\n"; }); ----
1803 return EmitBadPHI(); 0
1804 } ----
1805 ----
1806 return true; 0
1807 } ----
1808 ----
1809 void InstrRefBasedLDV::transferRegisterDef(MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1810 // Meta Instructions do not affect the debug liveness of any register they ----
1811 // define. ----
1812 if (MI.isImplicitDef()) { 0
1813 // Except when there's an implicit def, and the location it's defining has ----
1814 // no value number. The whole point of an implicit def is to announce that ----
1815 // the register is live, without be specific about it's value. So define ----
1816 // a value if there isn't one already. ----
1817 ValueIDNum Num = MTracker->readReg(MI.getOperand(0).getReg()); 0
1818 // Has a legitimate value -> ignore the implicit def. ----
1819 if (Num.getLoc() != 0) 0
1820 return; 0
1821 // Otherwise, def it here. ----
1822 } else if (MI.isMetaInstruction()) 0
1823 return; 0
1824 ----
1825 // We always ignore SP defines on call instructions, they don't actually ----
1826 // change the value of the stack pointer... except for win32's _chkstk. This ----
1827 // is rare: filter quickly for the common case (no stack adjustments, not a ----
1828 // call, etc). If it is a call that modifies SP, recognise the SP register ----
1829 // defs. ----
1830 bool CallChangesSP = false; 0
1831 if (AdjustsStackInCalls && MI.isCall() && MI.getOperand(0).isSymbol() && 0
1832 !strcmp(MI.getOperand(0).getSymbolName(), StackProbeSymbolName.data())) 0
1833 CallChangesSP = true; 0
1834 ----
1835 // Test whether we should ignore a def of this register due to it being part ----
1836 // of the stack pointer. ----
1837 auto IgnoreSPAlias = [this, &MI, CallChangesSP](Register R) -> bool { 0
1838 if (CallChangesSP) 0
1839 return false; 0
1840 return MI.isCall() && MTracker->SPAliases.count(R); 0
1841 }; 0
1842 ----
1843 // Find the regs killed by MI, and find regmasks of preserved regs. ----
1844 // Max out the number of statically allocated elements in `DeadRegs`, as this ----
1845 // prevents fallback to std::set::count() operations. ----
1846 SmallSet DeadRegs; 0
1847 SmallVector RegMasks; 0
1848 SmallVector RegMaskPtrs; 0
1849 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.operands()) { 0
1850 // Determine whether the operand is a register def. ----
1851 if (MO.isReg() && MO.isDef() && MO.getReg() && MO.getReg().isPhysical() && 0
1852 !IgnoreSPAlias(MO.getReg())) { 0
1853 // Remove ranges of all aliased registers. ----
1854 for (MCRegAliasIterator RAI(MO.getReg(), TRI, true); RAI.isValid(); ++RAI) 0
1855 // FIXME: Can we break out of this loop early if no insertion occurs? ----
1856 DeadRegs.insert(*RAI); 0
1857 } else if (MO.isRegMask()) { 0
1858 RegMasks.push_back(MO.getRegMask()); 0
1859 RegMaskPtrs.push_back(&MO); 0
1860 } ----
1861 } ----
1862 ----
1863 // Tell MLocTracker about all definitions, of regmasks and otherwise. ----
1864 for (uint32_t DeadReg : DeadRegs) 0
1865 MTracker->defReg(DeadReg, CurBB, CurInst); 0
1866 ----
1867 for (const auto *MO : RegMaskPtrs) 0
1868 MTracker->writeRegMask(MO, CurBB, CurInst); 0
1869 ----
1870 // If this instruction writes to a spill slot, def that slot. ----
1871 if (hasFoldedStackStore(MI)) { 0
1872 if (std::optional SpillNo = 0
1873 extractSpillBaseRegAndOffset(MI)) { 0
1874 for (unsigned int I = 0; I < MTracker->NumSlotIdxes; ++I) { 0
1875 unsigned SpillID = MTracker->getSpillIDWithIdx(*SpillNo, I); 0
1876 LocIdx L = MTracker->getSpillMLoc(SpillID); 0
1877 MTracker->setMLoc(L, ValueIDNum(CurBB, CurInst, L)); 0
1878 } ----
1879 } ----
1880 } ----
1881 ----
1882 if (!TTracker) 0
1883 return; 0
1884 ----
1885 // When committing variable values to locations: tell transfer tracker that ----
1886 // we've clobbered things. It may be able to recover the variable from a ----
1887 // different location. ----
1888 ----
1889 // Inform TTracker about any direct clobbers. ----
1890 for (uint32_t DeadReg : DeadRegs) { 0
1891 LocIdx Loc = MTracker->lookupOrTrackRegister(DeadReg); 0
1892 TTracker->clobberMloc(Loc, MI.getIterator(), false); 0
1893 } 0
1894 ----
1895 // Look for any clobbers performed by a register mask. Only test locations ----
1896 // that are actually being tracked. ----
1897 if (!RegMaskPtrs.empty()) { 0
1898 for (auto L : MTracker->locations()) { 0
1899 // Stack locations can't be clobbered by regmasks. ----
1900 if (MTracker->isSpill(L.Idx)) 0
1901 continue; 0
1902 ----
1903 Register Reg = MTracker->LocIdxToLocID[L.Idx]; 0
1904 if (IgnoreSPAlias(Reg)) 0
1905 continue; 0
1906 ----
1907 for (const auto *MO : RegMaskPtrs) 0
1908 if (MO->clobbersPhysReg(Reg)) 0
1909 TTracker->clobberMloc(L.Idx, MI.getIterator(), false); 0
1910 } ----
1911 } ----
1912 ----
1913 // Tell TTracker about any folded stack store. ----
1914 if (hasFoldedStackStore(MI)) { 0
1915 if (std::optional SpillNo = 0
1916 extractSpillBaseRegAndOffset(MI)) { 0
1917 for (unsigned int I = 0; I < MTracker->NumSlotIdxes; ++I) { 0
1918 unsigned SpillID = MTracker->getSpillIDWithIdx(*SpillNo, I); 0
1919 LocIdx L = MTracker->getSpillMLoc(SpillID); 0
1920 TTracker->clobberMloc(L, MI.getIterator(), true); 0
1921 } ----
1922 } ----
1923 } ----
1924 } 0
1925 ----
1926 void InstrRefBasedLDV::performCopy(Register SrcRegNum, Register DstRegNum) { 0
1927 // In all circumstances, re-def all aliases. It's definitely a new value now. ----
1928 for (MCRegAliasIterator RAI(DstRegNum, TRI, true); RAI.isValid(); ++RAI) 0
1929 MTracker->defReg(*RAI, CurBB, CurInst); 0
1930 ----
1931 ValueIDNum SrcValue = MTracker->readReg(SrcRegNum); 0
1932 MTracker->setReg(DstRegNum, SrcValue); 0
1933 ----
1934 // Copy subregisters from one location to another. ----
1935 for (MCSubRegIndexIterator SRI(SrcRegNum, TRI); SRI.isValid(); ++SRI) { 0
1936 unsigned SrcSubReg = SRI.getSubReg(); 0
1937 unsigned SubRegIdx = SRI.getSubRegIndex(); 0
1938 unsigned DstSubReg = TRI->getSubReg(DstRegNum, SubRegIdx); 0
1939 if (!DstSubReg) 0
1940 continue; 0
1941 ----
1942 // Do copy. There are two matching subregisters, the source value should ----
1943 // have been def'd when the super-reg was, the latter might not be tracked ----
1944 // yet. ----
1945 // This will force SrcSubReg to be tracked, if it isn't yet. Will read ----
1946 // mphi values if it wasn't tracked. ----
1947 LocIdx SrcL = MTracker->lookupOrTrackRegister(SrcSubReg); 0
1948 LocIdx DstL = MTracker->lookupOrTrackRegister(DstSubReg); 0
1949 (void)SrcL; ----
1950 (void)DstL; ----
1951 ValueIDNum CpyValue = MTracker->readReg(SrcSubReg); 0
1952 ----
1953 MTracker->setReg(DstSubReg, CpyValue); 0
1954 } ----
1955 } 0
1956 ----
1957 std::optional ----
1958 InstrRefBasedLDV::isSpillInstruction(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
1959 MachineFunction *MF) { ----
1960 // TODO: Handle multiple stores folded into one. ----
1961 if (!MI.hasOneMemOperand()) 0
1962 return std::nullopt; 0
1963 ----
1964 // Reject any memory operand that's aliased -- we can't guarantee its value. ----
1965 auto MMOI = MI.memoperands_begin(); 0
1966 const PseudoSourceValue *PVal = (*MMOI)->getPseudoValue(); 0
1967 if (PVal->isAliased(MFI)) 0
1968 return std::nullopt; 0
1969 ----
1970 if (!MI.getSpillSize(TII) && !MI.getFoldedSpillSize(TII)) 0
1971 return std::nullopt; // This is not a spill instruction, since no valid size 0
1972 // was returned from either function. ----
1973 ----
1974 return extractSpillBaseRegAndOffset(MI); 0
1975 } ----
1976 ----
1977 bool InstrRefBasedLDV::isLocationSpill(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
1978 MachineFunction *MF, unsigned &Reg) { ----
1979 if (!isSpillInstruction(MI, MF)) 0
1980 return false; 0
1981 ----
1982 int FI; ----
1983 Reg = TII->isStoreToStackSlotPostFE(MI, FI); 0
1984 return Reg != 0; 0
1985 } ----
1986 ----
1987 std::optional ----
1988 InstrRefBasedLDV::isRestoreInstruction(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
1989 MachineFunction *MF, unsigned &Reg) { ----
1990 if (!MI.hasOneMemOperand()) 0
1991 return std::nullopt; 0
1992 ----
1993 // FIXME: Handle folded restore instructions with more than one memory ----
1994 // operand. ----
1995 if (MI.getRestoreSize(TII)) { 0
1996 Reg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1997 return extractSpillBaseRegAndOffset(MI); 0
1998 } ----
1999 return std::nullopt; 0
2000 } ----
2001 ----
2002 bool InstrRefBasedLDV::transferSpillOrRestoreInst(MachineInstr &MI) { 0
2003 // XXX -- it's too difficult to implement VarLocBasedImpl's stack location ----
2004 // limitations under the new model. Therefore, when comparing them, compare ----
2005 // versions that don't attempt spills or restores at all. ----
2006 if (EmulateOldLDV) 0
2007 return false; 0
2008 ----
2009 // Strictly limit ourselves to plain loads and stores, not all instructions ----
2010 // that can access the stack. ----
2011 int DummyFI = -1; 0
2012 if (!TII->isStoreToStackSlotPostFE(MI, DummyFI) && 0
2013 !TII->isLoadFromStackSlotPostFE(MI, DummyFI)) 0
2014 return false; 0
2015 ----
2016 MachineFunction *MF = MI.getMF(); 0
2017 unsigned Reg; ----
2018 ----
2019 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Examining instruction: "; MI.dump();); 0
2020 ----
2021 // Strictly limit ourselves to plain loads and stores, not all instructions ----
2022 // that can access the stack. ----
2023 int FIDummy; ----
2024 if (!TII->isStoreToStackSlotPostFE(MI, FIDummy) && 0
2025 !TII->isLoadFromStackSlotPostFE(MI, FIDummy)) 0
2026 return false; 0
2027 ----
2028 // First, if there are any DBG_VALUEs pointing at a spill slot that is ----
2029 // written to, terminate that variable location. The value in memory ----
2030 // will have changed. DbgEntityHistoryCalculator doesn't try to detect this. ----
2031 if (std::optional Loc = isSpillInstruction(MI, MF)) { 0
2032 // Un-set this location and clobber, so that earlier locations don't ----
2033 // continue past this store. ----
2034 for (unsigned SlotIdx = 0; SlotIdx < MTracker->NumSlotIdxes; ++SlotIdx) { 0
2035 unsigned SpillID = MTracker->getSpillIDWithIdx(*Loc, SlotIdx); 0
2036 std::optional MLoc = MTracker->getSpillMLoc(SpillID); 0
2037 if (!MLoc) 0
2038 continue; 0
2039 ----
