2040 // We need to over-write the stack slot with something (here, a def at ----
2041 // this instruction) to ensure no values are preserved in this stack slot ----
2042 // after the spill. It also prevents TTracker from trying to recover the ----
2043 // location and re-installing it in the same place. ----
2044 ValueIDNum Def(CurBB, CurInst, *MLoc); 0
2045 MTracker->setMLoc(*MLoc, Def); 0
2046 if (TTracker) 0
2047 TTracker->clobberMloc(*MLoc, MI.getIterator()); 0
2048 } ----
2049 } ----
2050 ----
2051 // Try to recognise spill and restore instructions that may transfer a value. ----
2052 if (isLocationSpill(MI, MF, Reg)) { 0
2053 // isLocationSpill returning true should guarantee we can extract a ----
2054 // location. ----
2055 SpillLocationNo Loc = *extractSpillBaseRegAndOffset(MI); 0
2056 ----
2057 auto DoTransfer = [&](Register SrcReg, unsigned SpillID) { 0
2058 auto ReadValue = MTracker->readReg(SrcReg); 0
2059 LocIdx DstLoc = MTracker->getSpillMLoc(SpillID); 0
2060 MTracker->setMLoc(DstLoc, ReadValue); 0
2061 ----
2062 if (TTracker) { 0
2063 LocIdx SrcLoc = MTracker->getRegMLoc(SrcReg); 0
2064 TTracker->transferMlocs(SrcLoc, DstLoc, MI.getIterator()); 0
2065 } ----
2066 }; 0
2067 ----
2068 // Then, transfer subreg bits. ----
2069 for (MCPhysReg SR : TRI->subregs(Reg)) { 0
2070 // Ensure this reg is tracked, ----
2071 (void)MTracker->lookupOrTrackRegister(SR); 0
2072 unsigned SubregIdx = TRI->getSubRegIndex(Reg, SR); 0
2073 unsigned SpillID = MTracker->getLocID(Loc, SubregIdx); 0
2074 DoTransfer(SR, SpillID); 0
2075 } ----
2076 ----
2077 // Directly lookup size of main source reg, and transfer. ----
2078 unsigned Size = TRI->getRegSizeInBits(Reg, *MRI); 0
2079 unsigned SpillID = MTracker->getLocID(Loc, {Size, 0}); 0
2080 DoTransfer(Reg, SpillID); 0
2081 } else { ----
2082 std::optional Loc = isRestoreInstruction(MI, MF, Reg); 0
2083 if (!Loc) 0
2084 return false; 0
2085 ----
2086 // Assumption: we're reading from the base of the stack slot, not some ----
2087 // offset into it. It seems very unlikely LLVM would ever generate ----
2088 // restores where this wasn't true. This then becomes a question of what ----
2089 // subregisters in the destination register line up with positions in the ----
2090 // stack slot. ----
2091 ----
2092 // Def all registers that alias the destination. ----
2093 for (MCRegAliasIterator RAI(Reg, TRI, true); RAI.isValid(); ++RAI) 0
2094 MTracker->defReg(*RAI, CurBB, CurInst); 0
2095 ----
2096 // Now find subregisters within the destination register, and load values ----
2097 // from stack slot positions. ----
2098 auto DoTransfer = [&](Register DestReg, unsigned SpillID) { 0
2099 LocIdx SrcIdx = MTracker->getSpillMLoc(SpillID); 0
2100 auto ReadValue = MTracker->readMLoc(SrcIdx); 0
2101 MTracker->setReg(DestReg, ReadValue); 0
2102 }; 0
2103 ----
2104 for (MCPhysReg SR : TRI->subregs(Reg)) { 0
2105 unsigned Subreg = TRI->getSubRegIndex(Reg, SR); 0
2106 unsigned SpillID = MTracker->getLocID(*Loc, Subreg); 0
2107 DoTransfer(SR, SpillID); 0
2108 } ----
2109 ----
2110 // Directly look up this registers slot idx by size, and transfer. ----
2111 unsigned Size = TRI->getRegSizeInBits(Reg, *MRI); 0
2112 unsigned SpillID = MTracker->getLocID(*Loc, {Size, 0}); 0
2113 DoTransfer(Reg, SpillID); 0
2114 } ----
2115 return true; 0
2116 } ----
2117 ----
2118 bool InstrRefBasedLDV::transferRegisterCopy(MachineInstr &MI) { 0
2119 auto DestSrc = TII->isCopyInstr(MI); 0
2120 if (!DestSrc) 0
2121 return false; 0
2122 ----
2123 const MachineOperand *DestRegOp = DestSrc->Destination; 0
2124 const MachineOperand *SrcRegOp = DestSrc->Source; 0
2125 ----
2126 Register SrcReg = SrcRegOp->getReg(); 0
2127 Register DestReg = DestRegOp->getReg(); 0
2128 ----
2129 // Ignore identity copies. Yep, these make it as far as LiveDebugValues. ----
2130 if (SrcReg == DestReg) 0
2131 return true; 0
2132 ----
2133 // For emulating VarLocBasedImpl: ----
2134 // We want to recognize instructions where destination register is callee ----
2135 // saved register. If register that could be clobbered by the call is ----
2136 // included, there would be a great chance that it is going to be clobbered ----
2137 // soon. It is more likely that previous register, which is callee saved, is ----
2138 // going to stay unclobbered longer, even if it is killed. ----
2139 // ----
2140 // For InstrRefBasedImpl, we can track multiple locations per value, so ----
2141 // ignore this condition. ----
2142 if (EmulateOldLDV && !isCalleeSavedReg(DestReg)) 0
2143 return false; 0
2144 ----
2145 // InstrRefBasedImpl only followed killing copies. ----
2146 if (EmulateOldLDV && !SrcRegOp->isKill()) 0
2147 return false; 0
2148 ----
2149 // Before we update MTracker, remember which values were present in each of ----
2150 // the locations about to be overwritten, so that we can recover any ----
2151 // potentially clobbered variables. ----
2152 DenseMap ClobberedLocs; 0
2153 if (TTracker) { 0
2154 for (MCRegAliasIterator RAI(DestReg, TRI, true); RAI.isValid(); ++RAI) { 0
2155 LocIdx ClobberedLoc = MTracker->getRegMLoc(*RAI); 0
2156 auto MLocIt = TTracker->ActiveMLocs.find(ClobberedLoc); 0
2157 // If ActiveMLocs isn't tracking this location or there are no variables ----
2158 // using it, don't bother remembering. ----
2159 if (MLocIt == TTracker->ActiveMLocs.end() || MLocIt->second.empty()) 0
2160 continue; 0
2161 ValueIDNum Value = MTracker->readReg(*RAI); 0
2162 ClobberedLocs[ClobberedLoc] = Value; 0
2163 } ----
2164 } ----
2165 ----
2166 // Copy MTracker info, including subregs if available. ----
2167 InstrRefBasedLDV::performCopy(SrcReg, DestReg); 0
2168 ----
2169 // The copy might have clobbered variables based on the destination register. ----
2170 // Tell TTracker about it, passing the old ValueIDNum to search for ----
2171 // alternative locations (or else terminating those variables). ----
2172 if (TTracker) { 0
2173 for (auto LocVal : ClobberedLocs) { 0
2174 TTracker->clobberMloc(LocVal.first, LocVal.second, MI.getIterator(), false); 0
2175 } ----
2176 } ----
2177 ----
2178 // Only produce a transfer of DBG_VALUE within a block where old LDV ----
2179 // would have. We might make use of the additional value tracking in some ----
2180 // other way, later. ----
2181 if (TTracker && isCalleeSavedReg(DestReg) && SrcRegOp->isKill()) 0
2182 TTracker->transferMlocs(MTracker->getRegMLoc(SrcReg), 0
2183 MTracker->getRegMLoc(DestReg), MI.getIterator()); 0
2184 ----
2185 // VarLocBasedImpl would quit tracking the old location after copying. ----
2186 if (EmulateOldLDV && SrcReg != DestReg) 0
2187 MTracker->defReg(SrcReg, CurBB, CurInst); 0
2188 ----
2189 return true; 0
2190 } 0
2191 ----
2192 /// Accumulate a mapping between each DILocalVariable fragment and other ----
2193 /// fragments of that DILocalVariable which overlap. This reduces work during ----
2194 /// the data-flow stage from "Find any overlapping fragments" to "Check if the ----
2195 /// known-to-overlap fragments are present". ----
2196 /// \param MI A previously unprocessed debug instruction to analyze for ----
2197 /// fragment usage. ----
2198 void InstrRefBasedLDV::accumulateFragmentMap(MachineInstr &MI) { 0
2199 assert(MI.isDebugValueLike()); 0
2200 DebugVariable MIVar(MI.getDebugVariable(), MI.getDebugExpression(), ----
2201 MI.getDebugLoc()->getInlinedAt()); 0
2202 FragmentInfo ThisFragment = MIVar.getFragmentOrDefault(); 0
2203 ----
2204 // If this is the first sighting of this variable, then we are guaranteed ----
2205 // there are currently no overlapping fragments either. Initialize the set ----
2206 // of seen fragments, record no overlaps for the current one, and return. ----
2207 auto SeenIt = SeenFragments.find(MIVar.getVariable()); 0
2208 if (SeenIt == SeenFragments.end()) { 0
2209 SmallSet OneFragment; 0
2210 OneFragment.insert(ThisFragment); 0
2211 SeenFragments.insert({MIVar.getVariable(), OneFragment}); 0
2212 ----
2213 OverlapFragments.insert({{MIVar.getVariable(), ThisFragment}, {}}); 0
2214 return; 0
2215 } 0
2216 ----
2217 // If this particular Variable/Fragment pair already exists in the overlap ----
2218 // map, it has already been accounted for. ----
2219 auto IsInOLapMap = ----
2220 OverlapFragments.insert({{MIVar.getVariable(), ThisFragment}, {}}); 0
2221 if (!IsInOLapMap.second) 0
2222 return; 0
2223 ----
2224 auto &ThisFragmentsOverlaps = IsInOLapMap.first->second; 0
2225 auto &AllSeenFragments = SeenIt->second; 0
2226 ----
2227 // Otherwise, examine all other seen fragments for this variable, with "this" ----
2228 // fragment being a previously unseen fragment. Record any pair of ----
2229 // overlapping fragments. ----
2230 for (const auto &ASeenFragment : AllSeenFragments) { 0
2231 // Does this previously seen fragment overlap? ----
2232 if (DIExpression::fragmentsOverlap(ThisFragment, ASeenFragment)) { 0
2233 // Yes: Mark the current fragment as being overlapped. ----
2234 ThisFragmentsOverlaps.push_back(ASeenFragment); 0
2235 // Mark the previously seen fragment as being overlapped by the current ----
2236 // one. ----
2237 auto ASeenFragmentsOverlaps = ----
2238 OverlapFragments.find({MIVar.getVariable(), ASeenFragment}); 0
2239 assert(ASeenFragmentsOverlaps != OverlapFragments.end() && 0
2240 "Previously seen var fragment has no vector of overlaps"); ----
2241 ASeenFragmentsOverlaps->second.push_back(ThisFragment); 0
2242 } ----
2243 } 0
2244 ----
2245 AllSeenFragments.insert(ThisFragment); 0
2246 } ----
2247 ----
2248 void InstrRefBasedLDV::process(MachineInstr &MI, const ValueTable *MLiveOuts, 0
2249 const ValueTable *MLiveIns) { ----
2250 // Try to interpret an MI as a debug or transfer instruction. Only if it's ----
2251 // none of these should we interpret it's register defs as new value ----
2252 // definitions. ----
2253 if (transferDebugValue(MI)) 0
2254 return; 0
2255 if (transferDebugInstrRef(MI, MLiveOuts, MLiveIns)) 0
2256 return; 0
2257 if (transferDebugPHI(MI)) 0
2258 return; 0
2259 if (transferRegisterCopy(MI)) 0
2260 return; 0
2261 if (transferSpillOrRestoreInst(MI)) 0
2262 return; 0
2263 transferRegisterDef(MI); 0
2264 } ----
2265 ----
2266 void InstrRefBasedLDV::produceMLocTransferFunction( 0
2267 MachineFunction &MF, SmallVectorImpl &MLocTransfer, ----
2268 unsigned MaxNumBlocks) { ----
2269 // Because we try to optimize around register mask operands by ignoring regs ----
2270 // that aren't currently tracked, we set up something ugly for later: RegMask ----
2271 // operands that are seen earlier than the first use of a register, still need ----
2272 // to clobber that register in the transfer function. But this information ----
2273 // isn't actively recorded. Instead, we track each RegMask used in each block, ----
2274 // and accumulated the clobbered but untracked registers in each block into ----
2275 // the following bitvector. Later, if new values are tracked, we can add ----
2276 // appropriate clobbers. ----
2277 SmallVector BlockMasks; 0
2278 BlockMasks.resize(MaxNumBlocks); 0
2279 ----
2280 // Reserve one bit per register for the masks described above. ----
2281 unsigned BVWords = MachineOperand::getRegMaskSize(TRI->getNumRegs()); 0
2282 for (auto &BV : BlockMasks) 0
2283 BV.resize(TRI->getNumRegs(), true); 0
2284 ----
2285 // Step through all instructions and inhale the transfer function. ----
2286 for (auto &MBB : MF) { 0
2287 // Object fields that are read by trackers to know where we are in the ----
2288 // function. ----
2289 CurBB = MBB.getNumber(); 0
2290 CurInst = 1; 0
2291 ----
2292 // Set all machine locations to a PHI value. For transfer function ----
2293 // production only, this signifies the live-in value to the block. ----
2294 MTracker->reset(); 0
2295 MTracker->setMPhis(CurBB); 0
2296 ----
2297 // Step through each instruction in this block. ----
2298 for (auto &MI : MBB) { 0
2299 // Pass in an empty unique_ptr for the value tables when accumulating the ----
2300 // machine transfer function. ----
2301 process(MI, nullptr, nullptr); 0
2302 ----
2303 // Also accumulate fragment map. ----
2304 if (MI.isDebugValueLike()) 0
2305 accumulateFragmentMap(MI); 0
2306 ----
2307 // Create a map from the instruction number (if present) to the ----
2308 // MachineInstr and its position. ----
2309 if (uint64_t InstrNo = MI.peekDebugInstrNum()) { 0
2310 auto InstrAndPos = std::make_pair(&MI, CurInst); 0
2311 auto InsertResult = ----
2312 DebugInstrNumToInstr.insert(std::make_pair(InstrNo, InstrAndPos)); 0
2313 ----
2314 // There should never be duplicate instruction numbers. ----
2315 assert(InsertResult.second); 0
2316 (void)InsertResult; ----
2317 } ----
2318 ----
2319 ++CurInst; 0
2320 } ----
2321 ----
2322 // Produce the transfer function, a map of machine location to new value. If ----
2323 // any machine location has the live-in phi value from the start of the ----
2324 // block, it's live-through and doesn't need recording in the transfer ----
2325 // function. ----
2326 for (auto Location : MTracker->locations()) { 0
2327 LocIdx Idx = Location.Idx; 0
2328 ValueIDNum &P = Location.Value; 0
2329 if (P.isPHI() && P.getLoc() == Idx.asU64()) 0
2330 continue; 0
2331 ----
2332 // Insert-or-update. ----
2333 auto &TransferMap = MLocTransfer[CurBB]; 0
2334 auto Result = TransferMap.insert(std::make_pair(Idx.asU64(), P)); 0
2335 if (!Result.second) 0
2336 Result.first->second = P; 0
2337 } ----
2338 ----
2339 // Accumulate any bitmask operands into the clobbered reg mask for this ----
2340 // block. ----
2341 for (auto &P : MTracker->Masks) { 0
2342 BlockMasks[CurBB].clearBitsNotInMask(P.first->getRegMask(), BVWords); 0
2343 } ----
2344 } ----
2345 ----
2346 // Compute a bitvector of all the registers that are tracked in this block. ----
2347 BitVector UsedRegs(TRI->getNumRegs()); 0
2348 for (auto Location : MTracker->locations()) { 0
2349 unsigned ID = MTracker->LocIdxToLocID[Location.Idx]; 0
2350 // Ignore stack slots, and aliases of the stack pointer. ----
2351 if (ID >= TRI->getNumRegs() || MTracker->SPAliases.count(ID)) 0
2352 continue; 0
2353 UsedRegs.set(ID); 0
2354 } ----
2355 ----
2356 // Check that any regmask-clobber of a register that gets tracked, is not ----
2357 // live-through in the transfer function. It needs to be clobbered at the ----
2358 // very least. ----
2359 for (unsigned int I = 0; I < MaxNumBlocks; ++I) { 0
2360 BitVector &BV = BlockMasks[I]; 0
2361 BV.flip(); 0
2362 BV &= UsedRegs; 0
2363 // This produces all the bits that we clobber, but also use. Check that ----
2364 // they're all clobbered or at least set in the designated transfer ----
2365 // elem. ----
2366 for (unsigned Bit : BV.set_bits()) { 0
2367 unsigned ID = MTracker->getLocID(Bit); 0
2368 LocIdx Idx = MTracker->LocIDToLocIdx[ID]; 0
2369 auto &TransferMap = MLocTransfer[I]; 0
2370 ----
2371 // Install a value representing the fact that this location is effectively ----
2372 // written to in this block. As there's no reserved value, instead use ----
2373 // a value number that is never generated. Pick the value number for the ----
2374 // first instruction in the block, def'ing this location, which we know ----
2375 // this block never used anyway. ----
2376 ValueIDNum NotGeneratedNum = ValueIDNum(I, 1, Idx); 0
2377 auto Result = ----
2378 TransferMap.insert(std::make_pair(Idx.asU64(), NotGeneratedNum)); 0
2379 if (!Result.second) { 0
2380 ValueIDNum &ValueID = Result.first->second; 0
2381 if (ValueID.getBlock() == I && ValueID.isPHI()) 0
2382 // It was left as live-through. Set it to clobbered. ----
2383 ValueID = NotGeneratedNum; 0
2384 } ----
2385 } ----
2386 } ----
2387 } 0
2388 ----
2389 bool InstrRefBasedLDV::mlocJoin( 0
2390 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, SmallPtrSet &Visited, ----
2391 FuncValueTable &OutLocs, ValueTable &InLocs) { ----
2392 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "join MBB: " << MBB.getNumber() << "\n"); 0
2393 bool Changed = false; 0
2394 ----
2395 // Handle value-propagation when control flow merges on entry to a block. For ----
2396 // any location without a PHI already placed, the location has the same value ----
2397 // as its predecessors. If a PHI is placed, test to see whether it's now a ----
2398 // redundant PHI that we can eliminate. ----
2399 ----
2400 SmallVector BlockOrders; 0
2401 for (auto *Pred : MBB.predecessors()) 0
2402 BlockOrders.push_back(Pred); 0
2403 ----
2404 // Visit predecessors in RPOT order. ----
2405 auto Cmp = [&](const MachineBasicBlock *A, const MachineBasicBlock *B) { 0
2406 return BBToOrder.find(A)->second < BBToOrder.find(B)->second; 0
2407 }; 0
2408 llvm::sort(BlockOrders, Cmp); 0
2409 ----
2410 // Skip entry block. ----
2411 if (BlockOrders.size() == 0) 0
2412 return false; 0
2413 ----
2414 // Step through all machine locations, look at each predecessor and test ----
2415 // whether we can eliminate redundant PHIs. ----
2416 for (auto Location : MTracker->locations()) { 0
2417 LocIdx Idx = Location.Idx; 0
2418 ----
2419 // Pick out the first predecessors live-out value for this location. It's ----
2420 // guaranteed to not be a backedge, as we order by RPO. ----
2421 ValueIDNum FirstVal = OutLocs[BlockOrders[0]->getNumber()][Idx.asU64()]; 0
2422 ----
2423 // If we've already eliminated a PHI here, do no further checking, just ----
2424 // propagate the first live-in value into this block. ----
2425 if (InLocs[Idx.asU64()] != ValueIDNum(MBB.getNumber(), 0, Idx)) { 0
2426 if (InLocs[Idx.asU64()] != FirstVal) { 0
2427 InLocs[Idx.asU64()] = FirstVal; 0
2428 Changed |= true; 0
2429 } ----
2430 continue; 0
2431 } ----
2432 ----
2433 // We're now examining a PHI to see whether it's un-necessary. Loop around ----
2434 // the other live-in values and test whether they're all the same. ----
2435 bool Disagree = false; 0
2436 for (unsigned int I = 1; I < BlockOrders.size(); ++I) { 0
2437 const MachineBasicBlock *PredMBB = BlockOrders[I]; 0
2438 const ValueIDNum &PredLiveOut = ----
2439 OutLocs[PredMBB->getNumber()][Idx.asU64()]; 0
2440 ----
2441 // Incoming values agree, continue trying to eliminate this PHI. ----
2442 if (FirstVal == PredLiveOut) 0
2443 continue; 0
2444 ----
2445 // We can also accept a PHI value that feeds back into itself. ----
2446 if (PredLiveOut == ValueIDNum(MBB.getNumber(), 0, Idx)) 0
2447 continue; 0
2448 ----
2449 // Live-out of a predecessor disagrees with the first predecessor. ----
2450 Disagree = true; 0
2451 } ----
2452 ----
2453 // No disagreement? No PHI. Otherwise, leave the PHI in live-ins. ----
2454 if (!Disagree) { 0
2455 InLocs[Idx.asU64()] = FirstVal; 0
2456 Changed |= true; 0
2457 } ----
2458 } ----
2459 ----
2460 // TODO: Reimplement NumInserted and NumRemoved. ----
2461 return Changed; 0
2462 } 0
2463 ----
2464 void InstrRefBasedLDV::findStackIndexInterference( 0
2465 SmallVectorImpl &Slots) { ----
2466 // We could spend a bit of time finding the exact, minimal, set of stack ----
2467 // indexes that interfere with each other, much like reg units. Or, we can ----
2468 // rely on the fact that: ----
2469 // * The smallest / lowest index will interfere with everything at zero ----
2470 // offset, which will be the largest set of registers, ----
2471 // * Most indexes with non-zero offset will end up being interference units ----
2472 // anyway. ----
2473 // So just pick those out and return them. ----
2474 ----
2475 // We can rely on a single-byte stack index existing already, because we ----
2476 // initialize them in MLocTracker. ----
2477 auto It = MTracker->StackSlotIdxes.find({8, 0}); 0
2478 assert(It != MTracker->StackSlotIdxes.end()); 0
2479 Slots.push_back(It->second); 0
2480 ----
2481 // Find anything that has a non-zero offset and add that too. ----
2482 for (auto &Pair : MTracker->StackSlotIdxes) { 0
2483 // Is offset zero? If so, ignore. ----
2484 if (!Pair.first.second) 0
2485 continue; 0
2486 Slots.push_back(Pair.second); 0
2487 } ----
2488 } 0
2489 ----
2490 void InstrRefBasedLDV::placeMLocPHIs( 0
2491 MachineFunction &MF, SmallPtrSetImpl &AllBlocks, ----
2492 FuncValueTable &MInLocs, SmallVectorImpl &MLocTransfer) { ----
2493 SmallVector StackUnits; 0
2494 findStackIndexInterference(StackUnits); 0
2495 ----
2496 // To avoid repeatedly running the PHI placement algorithm, leverage the ----
2497 // fact that a def of register MUST also def its register units. Find the ----
2498 // units for registers, place PHIs for them, and then replicate them for ----
2499 // aliasing registers. Some inputs that are never def'd (DBG_PHIs of ----
2500 // arguments) don't lead to register units being tracked, just place PHIs for ----
2501 // those registers directly. Stack slots have their own form of "unit", ----
2502 // store them to one side. ----
2503 SmallSet RegUnitsToPHIUp; 0
2504 SmallSet NormalLocsToPHI; 0
2505 SmallSet StackSlots; 0
2506 for (auto Location : MTracker->locations()) { 0
2507 LocIdx L = Location.Idx; 0
2508 if (MTracker->isSpill(L)) { 0
2509 StackSlots.insert(MTracker->locIDToSpill(MTracker->LocIdxToLocID[L])); 0
2510 continue; 0
2511 } ----
2512 ----
2513 Register R = MTracker->LocIdxToLocID[L]; 0
2514 SmallSet FoundRegUnits; 0
2515 bool AnyIllegal = false; 0
2516 for (MCRegUnit Unit : TRI->regunits(R.asMCReg())) { 0
2517 for (MCRegUnitRootIterator URoot(Unit, TRI); URoot.isValid(); ++URoot) { 0
2518 if (!MTracker->isRegisterTracked(*URoot)) { 0
2519 // Not all roots were loaded into the tracking map: this register ----
2520 // isn't actually def'd anywhere, we only read from it. Generate PHIs ----
2521 // for this reg, but don't iterate units. ----
2522 AnyIllegal = true; 0
2523 } else { ----
2524 FoundRegUnits.insert(*URoot); 0
2525 } ----
2526 } ----
2527 } ----
2528 ----
2529 if (AnyIllegal) { 0
2530 NormalLocsToPHI.insert(L); 0
2531 continue; 0
2532 } ----
2533 ----
2534 RegUnitsToPHIUp.insert(FoundRegUnits.begin(), FoundRegUnits.end()); 0
2535 } 0
2536 ----
2537 // Lambda to fetch PHIs for a given location, and write into the PHIBlocks ----
2538 // collection. ----
2539 SmallVector PHIBlocks; 0
2540 auto CollectPHIsForLoc = [&](LocIdx L) { 0
2541 // Collect the set of defs. ----
2542 SmallPtrSet DefBlocks; 0
2543 for (unsigned int I = 0; I < OrderToBB.size(); ++I) { 0
2544 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = OrderToBB[I]; 0
2545 const auto &TransferFunc = MLocTransfer[MBB->getNumber()]; 0
2546 if (TransferFunc.find(L) != TransferFunc.end()) 0
2547 DefBlocks.insert(MBB); 0
2548 } ----
2549 ----
2550 // The entry block defs the location too: it's the live-in / argument value. ----
2551 // Only insert if there are other defs though; everything is trivially live ----
2552 // through otherwise. ----
2553 if (!DefBlocks.empty()) 0
2554 DefBlocks.insert(&*MF.begin()); 0
2555 ----
2556 // Ask the SSA construction algorithm where we should put PHIs. Clear ----
2557 // anything that might have been hanging around from earlier. ----
2558 PHIBlocks.clear(); 0
2559 BlockPHIPlacement(AllBlocks, DefBlocks, PHIBlocks); 0
2560 }; 0
2561 ----
2562 auto InstallPHIsAtLoc = [&PHIBlocks, &MInLocs](LocIdx L) { 0
2563 for (const MachineBasicBlock *MBB : PHIBlocks) 0
2564 MInLocs[MBB->getNumber()][L.asU64()] = ValueIDNum(MBB->getNumber(), 0, L); 0
2565 }; 0
2566 ----
2567 // For locations with no reg units, just place PHIs. ----
2568 for (LocIdx L : NormalLocsToPHI) { 0
2569 CollectPHIsForLoc(L); 0
2570 // Install those PHI values into the live-in value array. ----
2571 InstallPHIsAtLoc(L); 0
2572 } 0
2573 ----
2574 // For stack slots, calculate PHIs for the equivalent of the units, then ----
2575 // install for each index. ----
2576 for (SpillLocationNo Slot : StackSlots) { 0
2577 for (unsigned Idx : StackUnits) { 0
2578 unsigned SpillID = MTracker->getSpillIDWithIdx(Slot, Idx); 0
2579 LocIdx L = MTracker->getSpillMLoc(SpillID); 0
2580 CollectPHIsForLoc(L); 0
2581 InstallPHIsAtLoc(L); 0
2582 ----
2583 // Find anything that aliases this stack index, install PHIs for it too. ----
2584 unsigned Size, Offset; ----
2585 std::tie(Size, Offset) = MTracker->StackIdxesToPos[Idx]; 0
2586 for (auto &Pair : MTracker->StackSlotIdxes) { 0
2587 unsigned ThisSize, ThisOffset; ----
2588 std::tie(ThisSize, ThisOffset) = Pair.first; 0
2589 if (ThisSize + ThisOffset <= Offset || Size + Offset <= ThisOffset) 0
2590 continue; 0
2591 ----
2592 unsigned ThisID = MTracker->getSpillIDWithIdx(Slot, Pair.second); 0
2593 LocIdx ThisL = MTracker->getSpillMLoc(ThisID); 0
2594 InstallPHIsAtLoc(ThisL); 0
2595 } ----
2596 } ----
2597 } 0
2598 ----
2599 // For reg units, place PHIs, and then place them for any aliasing registers. ----
2600 for (Register R : RegUnitsToPHIUp) { 0
2601 LocIdx L = MTracker->lookupOrTrackRegister(R); 0
2602 CollectPHIsForLoc(L); 0
2603 ----
2604 // Install those PHI values into the live-in value array. ----
2605 InstallPHIsAtLoc(L); 0
2606 ----
2607 // Now find aliases and install PHIs for those. ----
2608 for (MCRegAliasIterator RAI(R, TRI, true); RAI.isValid(); ++RAI) { 0
2609 // Super-registers that are "above" the largest register read/written by ----
2610 // the function will alias, but will not be tracked. ----
2611 if (!MTracker->isRegisterTracked(*RAI)) 0
2612 continue; 0
2613 ----
2614 LocIdx AliasLoc = MTracker->lookupOrTrackRegister(*RAI); 0
2615 InstallPHIsAtLoc(AliasLoc); 0
2616 } ----
2617 } 0
2618 } 0
2619 ----
2620 void InstrRefBasedLDV::buildMLocValueMap( 0
2621 MachineFunction &MF, FuncValueTable &MInLocs, FuncValueTable &MOutLocs, ----
2622 SmallVectorImpl &MLocTransfer) { ----
2623 std::priority_queue, ----
2624 std::greater> ----
2625 Worklist, Pending; 0
2626 ----
2627 // We track what is on the current and pending worklist to avoid inserting ----
2628 // the same thing twice. We could avoid this with a custom priority queue, ----
2629 // but this is probably not worth it. ----
2630 SmallPtrSet OnPending, OnWorklist; 0
2631 ----
2632 // Initialize worklist with every block to be visited. Also produce list of ----
2633 // all blocks. ----
2634 SmallPtrSet AllBlocks; 0
2635 for (unsigned int I = 0; I < BBToOrder.size(); ++I) { 0
2636 Worklist.push(I); 0
2637 OnWorklist.insert(OrderToBB[I]); 0
2638 AllBlocks.insert(OrderToBB[I]); 0
2639 } ----
2640 ----
2641 // Initialize entry block to PHIs. These represent arguments. ----
2642 for (auto Location : MTracker->locations()) 0
2643 MInLocs[0][Location.Idx.asU64()] = ValueIDNum(0, 0, Location.Idx); 0
2644 ----
2645 MTracker->reset(); 0
2646 ----
2647 // Start by placing PHIs, using the usual SSA constructor algorithm. Consider ----
2648 // any machine-location that isn't live-through a block to be def'd in that ----
2649 // block. ----
2650 placeMLocPHIs(MF, AllBlocks, MInLocs, MLocTransfer); 0
2651 ----
2652 // Propagate values to eliminate redundant PHIs. At the same time, this ----
2653 // produces the table of Block x Location => Value for the entry to each ----
2654 // block. ----
2655 // The kind of PHIs we can eliminate are, for example, where one path in a ----
2656 // conditional spills and restores a register, and the register still has ----
2657 // the same value once control flow joins, unbeknowns to the PHI placement ----
2658 // code. Propagating values allows us to identify such un-necessary PHIs and ----
2659 // remove them. ----
2660 SmallPtrSet Visited; 0
2661 while (!Worklist.empty() || !Pending.empty()) { 0
2662 // Vector for storing the evaluated block transfer function. ----
2663 SmallVector, 32> ToRemap; 0
2664 ----
2665 while (!Worklist.empty()) { 0
2666 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = OrderToBB[Worklist.top()]; 0
2667 CurBB = MBB->getNumber(); 0
2668 Worklist.pop(); 0
2669 ----
2670 // Join the values in all predecessor blocks. ----
2671 bool InLocsChanged; ----
2672 InLocsChanged = mlocJoin(*MBB, Visited, MOutLocs, MInLocs[CurBB]); 0
2673 InLocsChanged |= Visited.insert(MBB).second; 0
2674 ----
2675 // Don't examine transfer function if we've visited this loc at least ----
2676 // once, and inlocs haven't changed. ----
2677 if (!InLocsChanged) 0
2678 continue; 0
2679 ----
2680 // Load the current set of live-ins into MLocTracker. ----
2681 MTracker->loadFromArray(MInLocs[CurBB], CurBB); 0
2682 ----
2683 // Each element of the transfer function can be a new def, or a read of ----
2684 // a live-in value. Evaluate each element, and store to "ToRemap". ----
2685 ToRemap.clear(); 0
2686 for (auto &P : MLocTransfer[CurBB]) { 0
2687 if (P.second.getBlock() == CurBB && P.second.isPHI()) { 0
2688 // This is a movement of whatever was live in. Read it. ----
2689 ValueIDNum NewID = MTracker->readMLoc(P.second.getLoc()); 0
2690 ToRemap.push_back(std::make_pair(P.first, NewID)); 0
2691 } else { ----
2692 // It's a def. Just set it. ----
2693 assert(P.second.getBlock() == CurBB); 0
2694 ToRemap.push_back(std::make_pair(P.first, P.second)); 0
2695 } ----
2696 } ----
2697 ----
2698 // Commit the transfer function changes into mloc tracker, which ----
2699 // transforms the contents of the MLocTracker into the live-outs. ----
2700 for (auto &P : ToRemap) 0
2701 MTracker->setMLoc(P.first, P.second); 0
2702 ----
2703 // Now copy out-locs from mloc tracker into out-loc vector, checking ----
2704 // whether changes have occurred. These changes can have come from both ----
2705 // the transfer function, and mlocJoin. ----
2706 bool OLChanged = false; 0
2707 for (auto Location : MTracker->locations()) { 0
2708 OLChanged |= MOutLocs[CurBB][Location.Idx.asU64()] != Location.Value; 0
2709 MOutLocs[CurBB][Location.Idx.asU64()] = Location.Value; 0
2710 } ----
2711 ----
2712 MTracker->reset(); 0
2713 ----
2714 // No need to examine successors again if out-locs didn't change. ----
2715 if (!OLChanged) 0
2716 continue; 0
2717 ----
2718 // All successors should be visited: put any back-edges on the pending ----
2719 // list for the next pass-through, and any other successors to be ----
2720 // visited this pass, if they're not going to be already. ----
2721 for (auto *s : MBB->successors()) { 0
2722 // Does branching to this successor represent a back-edge? ----
2723 if (BBToOrder[s] > BBToOrder[MBB]) { 0
2724 // No: visit it during this dataflow iteration. ----
2725 if (OnWorklist.insert(s).second) 0
2726 Worklist.push(BBToOrder[s]); 0
2727 } else { ----
2728 // Yes: visit it on the next iteration. ----
2729 if (OnPending.insert(s).second) 0
2730 Pending.push(BBToOrder[s]); 0
2731 } ----
2732 } ----
2733 } ----
2734 ----
2735 Worklist.swap(Pending); 0
2736 std::swap(OnPending, OnWorklist); 0
2737 OnPending.clear(); 0
2738 // At this point, pending must be empty, since it was just the empty ----
2739 // worklist ----
2740 assert(Pending.empty() && "Pending should be empty"); 0
2741 } 0
2742 ----
2743 // Once all the live-ins don't change on mlocJoin(), we've eliminated all ----
2744 // redundant PHIs. ----
2745 } 0
2746 ----
2747 void InstrRefBasedLDV::BlockPHIPlacement( 0
2748 const SmallPtrSetImpl &AllBlocks, ----
2749 const SmallPtrSetImpl &DefBlocks, ----
2750 SmallVectorImpl &PHIBlocks) { ----
2751 // Apply IDF calculator to the designated set of location defs, storing ----
2752 // required PHIs into PHIBlocks. Uses the dominator tree stored in the ----
2753 // InstrRefBasedLDV object. ----
2754 IDFCalculatorBase IDF(DomTree->getBase()); 0
2755 ----
2756 IDF.setLiveInBlocks(AllBlocks); 0
2757 IDF.setDefiningBlocks(DefBlocks); 0
2758 IDF.calculate(PHIBlocks); 0
2759 } 0
2760 ----
2761 bool InstrRefBasedLDV::pickVPHILoc( 0
2762 SmallVectorImpl &OutValues, const MachineBasicBlock &MBB, ----
2763 const LiveIdxT &LiveOuts, FuncValueTable &MOutLocs, ----
2764 const SmallVectorImpl &BlockOrders) { ----
2765 ----
2766 // No predecessors means no PHIs. ----
2767 if (BlockOrders.empty()) 0
2768 return false; 0
2769 ----
2770 // All the location operands that do not already agree need to be joined, ----
2771 // track the indices of each such location operand here. ----
2772 SmallDenseSet LocOpsToJoin; 0
2773 ----
2774 auto FirstValueIt = LiveOuts.find(BlockOrders[0]); 0
2775 if (FirstValueIt == LiveOuts.end()) 0
2776 return false; 0
2777 const DbgValue &FirstValue = *FirstValueIt->second; 0
2778 ----
2779 for (const auto p : BlockOrders) { 0
2780 auto OutValIt = LiveOuts.find(p); 0
2781 if (OutValIt == LiveOuts.end()) 0
2782 // If we have a predecessor not in scope, we'll never find a PHI position. ----
2783 return false; 0
2784 const DbgValue &OutVal = *OutValIt->second; 0
2785 ----
2786 // No-values cannot have locations we can join on. ----
2787 if (OutVal.Kind == DbgValue::NoVal) 0
2788 return false; 0
2789 ----
2790 // For unjoined VPHIs where we don't know the location, we definitely ----
2791 // can't find a join loc unless the VPHI is a backedge. ----
2792 if (OutVal.isUnjoinedPHI() && OutVal.BlockNo != MBB.getNumber()) 0
2793 return false; 0
2794 ----
2795 if (!FirstValue.Properties.isJoinable(OutVal.Properties)) 0
2796 return false; 0
2797 ----
2798 for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx < FirstValue.getLocationOpCount(); ++Idx) { 0
2799 // An unjoined PHI has no defined locations, and so a shared location must ----
2800 // be found for every operand. ----
2801 if (OutVal.isUnjoinedPHI()) { 0
2802 LocOpsToJoin.insert(Idx); 0
2803 continue; 0
2804 } ----
2805 DbgOpID FirstValOp = FirstValue.getDbgOpID(Idx); 0
2806 DbgOpID OutValOp = OutVal.getDbgOpID(Idx); 0
2807 if (FirstValOp != OutValOp) { 0
2808 // We can never join constant ops - the ops must either both be equal ----
2809 // constant ops or non-const ops. ----
2810 if (FirstValOp.isConst() || OutValOp.isConst()) 0
2811 return false; 0
2812 else ----
2813 LocOpsToJoin.insert(Idx); 0
2814 } ----
2815 } ----
2816 } ----
2817 ----
2818 SmallVector NewDbgOps; 0
2819 ----
2820 for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx < FirstValue.getLocationOpCount(); ++Idx) { 0
2821 // If this op doesn't need to be joined because the values agree, use that ----
2822 // already-agreed value. ----
2823 if (!LocOpsToJoin.contains(Idx)) { 0
2824 NewDbgOps.push_back(FirstValue.getDbgOpID(Idx)); 0
2825 continue; 0
2826 } ----
2827 ----
2828 std::optional JoinedOpLoc = ----
2829 pickOperandPHILoc(Idx, MBB, LiveOuts, MOutLocs, BlockOrders); 0
2830 ----
2831 if (!JoinedOpLoc) 0
2832 return false; 0
2833 ----
2834 NewDbgOps.push_back(DbgOpStore.insert(*JoinedOpLoc)); 0
2835 } ----
2836 ----
2837 OutValues.append(NewDbgOps); 0
2838 return true; 0
2839 } 0
2840 ----
2841 std::optional InstrRefBasedLDV::pickOperandPHILoc( 0
2842 unsigned DbgOpIdx, const MachineBasicBlock &MBB, const LiveIdxT &LiveOuts, ----
2843 FuncValueTable &MOutLocs, ----
2844 const SmallVectorImpl &BlockOrders) { ----
2845 ----
2846 // Collect a set of locations from predecessor where its live-out value can ----
2847 // be found. ----
2848 SmallVector, 8> Locs; 0
2849 unsigned NumLocs = MTracker->getNumLocs(); 0
2850 ----
2851 for (const auto p : BlockOrders) { 0
2852 unsigned ThisBBNum = p->getNumber(); 0
2853 auto OutValIt = LiveOuts.find(p); 0
2854 assert(OutValIt != LiveOuts.end()); 0
2855 const DbgValue &OutVal = *OutValIt->second; 0
2856 DbgOpID OutValOpID = OutVal.getDbgOpID(DbgOpIdx); 0
2857 DbgOp OutValOp = DbgOpStore.find(OutValOpID); 0
2858 assert(!OutValOp.IsConst); 0
2859 ----
2860 // Create new empty vector of locations. ----
2861 Locs.resize(Locs.size() + 1); 0
2862 ----
2863 // If the live-in value is a def, find the locations where that value is ----
2864 // present. Do the same for VPHIs where we know the VPHI value. ----
2865 if (OutVal.Kind == DbgValue::Def || 0
2866 (OutVal.Kind == DbgValue::VPHI && OutVal.BlockNo != MBB.getNumber() && 0
2867 !OutValOp.isUndef())) { 0
2868 ValueIDNum ValToLookFor = OutValOp.ID; 0
2869 // Search the live-outs of the predecessor for the specified value. ----
2870 for (unsigned int I = 0; I < NumLocs; ++I) { 0
2871 if (MOutLocs[ThisBBNum][I] == ValToLookFor) 0
2872 Locs.back().push_back(LocIdx(I)); 0
2873 } ----
2874 } else { ----
2875 assert(OutVal.Kind == DbgValue::VPHI); 0
2876 // Otherwise: this is a VPHI on a backedge feeding back into itself, i.e. ----
2877 // a value that's live-through the whole loop. (It has to be a backedge, ----
2878 // because a block can't dominate itself). We can accept as a PHI location ----
2879 // any location where the other predecessors agree, _and_ the machine ----
2880 // locations feed back into themselves. Therefore, add all self-looping ----
2881 // machine-value PHI locations. ----
2882 for (unsigned int I = 0; I < NumLocs; ++I) { 0
2883 ValueIDNum MPHI(MBB.getNumber(), 0, LocIdx(I)); 0
2884 if (MOutLocs[ThisBBNum][I] == MPHI) 0
2885 Locs.back().push_back(LocIdx(I)); 0
2886 } ----
2887 } ----
2888 } ----
2889 // We should have found locations for all predecessors, or returned. ----
2890 assert(Locs.size() == BlockOrders.size()); 0
2891 ----
2892 // Starting with the first set of locations, take the intersection with ----
2893 // subsequent sets. ----
2894 SmallVector CandidateLocs = Locs[0]; 0
2895 for (unsigned int I = 1; I < Locs.size(); ++I) { 0
2896 auto &LocVec = Locs[I]; 0
2897 SmallVector NewCandidates; 0
2898 std::set_intersection(CandidateLocs.begin(), CandidateLocs.end(), 0
2899 LocVec.begin(), LocVec.end(), std::inserter(NewCandidates, NewCandidates.begin())); ----
2900 CandidateLocs = NewCandidates; 0
2901 } 0
2902 if (CandidateLocs.empty()) 0
2903 return std::nullopt; 0
2904 ----
2905 // We now have a set of LocIdxes that contain the right output value in ----
2906 // each of the predecessors. Pick the lowest; if there's a register loc, ----
2907 // that'll be it. ----
2908 LocIdx L = *CandidateLocs.begin(); 0
2909 ----
2910 // Return a PHI-value-number for the found location. ----
2911 ValueIDNum PHIVal = {(unsigned)MBB.getNumber(), 0, L}; 0
2912 return PHIVal; 0
2913 } 0
2914 ----
2915 bool InstrRefBasedLDV::vlocJoin( 0
2916 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, LiveIdxT &VLOCOutLocs, ----
2917 SmallPtrSet &BlocksToExplore, ----
2918 DbgValue &LiveIn) { ----
2919 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "join MBB: " << MBB.getNumber() << "\n"); 0
2920 bool Changed = false; 0
2921 ----
2922 // Order predecessors by RPOT order, for exploring them in that order. ----
2923 SmallVector BlockOrders(MBB.predecessors()); 0
2924 ----
2925 auto Cmp = [&](MachineBasicBlock *A, MachineBasicBlock *B) { 0
2926 return BBToOrder[A] < BBToOrder[B]; 0
2927 }; 0
2928 ----
2929 llvm::sort(BlockOrders, Cmp); 0
2930 ----
2931 unsigned CurBlockRPONum = BBToOrder[&MBB]; 0
2932 ----
2933 // Collect all the incoming DbgValues for this variable, from predecessor ----
2934 // live-out values. ----
2935 SmallVector Values; 0
2936 bool Bail = false; 0
2937 int BackEdgesStart = 0; 0
2938 for (auto *p : BlockOrders) { 0
2939 // If the predecessor isn't in scope / to be explored, we'll never be ----
2940 // able to join any locations. ----
2941 if (!BlocksToExplore.contains(p)) { 0
2942 Bail = true; 0
2943 break; 0
2944 } ----
2945 ----
2946 // All Live-outs will have been initialized. ----
2947 DbgValue &OutLoc = *VLOCOutLocs.find(p)->second; 0
2948 ----
2949 // Keep track of where back-edges begin in the Values vector. Relies on ----
2950 // BlockOrders being sorted by RPO. ----
2951 unsigned ThisBBRPONum = BBToOrder[p]; 0
2952 if (ThisBBRPONum < CurBlockRPONum) 0
2953 ++BackEdgesStart; 0
2954 ----
2955 Values.push_back(std::make_pair(p, &OutLoc)); 0
2956 } ----
2957 ----
2958 // If there were no values, or one of the predecessors couldn't have a ----
2959 // value, then give up immediately. It's not safe to produce a live-in ----
2960 // value. Leave as whatever it was before. ----
2961 if (Bail || Values.size() == 0) 0
2962 return false; 0
2963 ----
2964 // All (non-entry) blocks have at least one non-backedge predecessor. ----
2965 // Pick the variable value from the first of these, to compare against ----
2966 // all others. ----
2967 const DbgValue &FirstVal = *Values[0].second; 0
2968 ----
2969 // If the old live-in value is not a PHI then either a) no PHI is needed ----
2970 // here, or b) we eliminated the PHI that was here. If so, we can just ----
2971 // propagate in the first parent's incoming value. ----
2972 if (LiveIn.Kind != DbgValue::VPHI || LiveIn.BlockNo != MBB.getNumber()) { 0
2973 Changed = LiveIn != FirstVal; 0
2974 if (Changed) 0
2975 LiveIn = FirstVal; 0
2976 return Changed; 0
2977 } ----
2978 ----
2979 // Scan for variable values that can never be resolved: if they have ----
2980 // different DIExpressions, different indirectness, or are mixed constants / ----
2981 // non-constants. ----
2982 for (const auto &V : Values) { 0
2983 if (!V.second->Properties.isJoinable(FirstVal.Properties)) 0
2984 return false; 0
2985 if (V.second->Kind == DbgValue::NoVal) 0
2986 return false; 0
2987 if (!V.second->hasJoinableLocOps(FirstVal)) 0
2988 return false; 0
2989 } ----
2990 ----
2991 // Try to eliminate this PHI. Do the incoming values all agree? ----
2992 bool Disagree = false; 0
2993 for (auto &V : Values) { 0
2994 if (*V.second == FirstVal) 0
2995 continue; // No disagreement. 0
2996 ----
2997 // If both values are not equal but have equal non-empty IDs then they refer ----
2998 // to the same value from different sources (e.g. one is VPHI and the other ----
2999 // is Def), which does not cause disagreement. ----
3000 if (V.second->hasIdenticalValidLocOps(FirstVal)) 0
3001 continue; 0
3002 ----
3003 // Eliminate if a backedge feeds a VPHI back into itself. ----
3004 if (V.second->Kind == DbgValue::VPHI && 0
3005 V.second->BlockNo == MBB.getNumber() && 0
3006 // Is this a backedge? ----
3007 std::distance(Values.begin(), &V) >= BackEdgesStart) 0
3008 continue; 0
3009 ----
3010 Disagree = true; 0
3011 } ----
3012 ----
3013 // No disagreement -> live-through value. ----
3014 if (!Disagree) { 0
3015 Changed = LiveIn != FirstVal; 0
3016 if (Changed) 0
3017 LiveIn = FirstVal; 0
3018 return Changed; 0
3019 } else { ----
3020 // Otherwise use a VPHI. ----
3021 DbgValue VPHI(MBB.getNumber(), FirstVal.Properties, DbgValue::VPHI); 0
3022 Changed = LiveIn != VPHI; 0
3023 if (Changed) 0
3024 LiveIn = VPHI; 0
3025 return Changed; 0
3026 } ----
3027 } 0
3028 ----
3029 void InstrRefBasedLDV::getBlocksForScope( 0
3030 const DILocation *DILoc, ----
3031 SmallPtrSetImpl &BlocksToExplore, ----
3032 const SmallPtrSetImpl &AssignBlocks) { ----
3033 // Get the set of "normal" in-lexical-scope blocks. ----
3034 LS.getMachineBasicBlocks(DILoc, BlocksToExplore); 0
3035 ----
3036 // VarLoc LiveDebugValues tracks variable locations that are defined in ----
3037 // blocks not in scope. This is something we could legitimately ignore, but ----
3038 // lets allow it for now for the sake of coverage. ----
3039 BlocksToExplore.insert(AssignBlocks.begin(), AssignBlocks.end()); 0
3040 ----
3041 // Storage for artificial blocks we intend to add to BlocksToExplore. ----
3042 DenseSet ToAdd; 0
3043 ----
3044 // To avoid needlessly dropping large volumes of variable locations, propagate ----
3045 // variables through aritifical blocks, i.e. those that don't have any ----
3046 // instructions in scope at all. To accurately replicate VarLoc ----
3047 // LiveDebugValues, this means exploring all artificial successors too. ----
3048 // Perform a depth-first-search to enumerate those blocks. ----
3049 for (const auto *MBB : BlocksToExplore) { 0
3050 // Depth-first-search state: each node is a block and which successor ----
3051 // we're currently exploring. ----
3052 SmallVector ----
3053 MachineBasicBlock::const_succ_iterator>, ----
3054 8> ----
3055 DFS; 0
3056 ----
3057 // Find any artificial successors not already tracked. ----
3058 for (auto *succ : MBB->successors()) { 0
3059 if (BlocksToExplore.count(succ)) 0
3060 continue; 0
3061 if (!ArtificialBlocks.count(succ)) 0
3062 continue; 0
3063 ToAdd.insert(succ); 0
3064 DFS.push_back({succ, succ->succ_begin()}); 0
3065 } ----
3066 ----
3067 // Search all those blocks, depth first. ----
3068 while (!DFS.empty()) { 0
3069 const MachineBasicBlock *CurBB = DFS.back().first; 0
3070 MachineBasicBlock::const_succ_iterator &CurSucc = DFS.back().second; 0
3071 // Walk back if we've explored this blocks successors to the end. ----
3072 if (CurSucc == CurBB->succ_end()) { 0
3073 DFS.pop_back(); 0
3074 continue; 0
3075 } ----
3076 ----
3077 // If the current successor is artificial and unexplored, descend into ----
3078 // it. ----
3079 if (!ToAdd.count(*CurSucc) && ArtificialBlocks.count(*CurSucc)) { 0
3080 ToAdd.insert(*CurSucc); 0
3081 DFS.push_back({*CurSucc, (*CurSucc)->succ_begin()}); 0
3082 continue; 0
3083 } ----
3084 ----
3085 ++CurSucc; 0
3086 } ----
3087 }; 0
3088 ----
3089 BlocksToExplore.insert(ToAdd.begin(), ToAdd.end()); 0
3090 } 0
3091 ----
3092 void InstrRefBasedLDV::buildVLocValueMap( 0
3093 const DILocation *DILoc, const SmallSet &VarsWeCareAbout, ----
3094 SmallPtrSetImpl &AssignBlocks, LiveInsT &Output, ----
3095 FuncValueTable &MOutLocs, FuncValueTable &MInLocs, ----
3096 SmallVectorImpl &AllTheVLocs) { ----
3097 // This method is much like buildMLocValueMap: but focuses on a single ----
3098 // LexicalScope at a time. Pick out a set of blocks and variables that are ----
3099 // to have their value assignments solved, then run our dataflow algorithm ----
3100 // until a fixedpoint is reached. ----
3101 std::priority_queue, ----
3102 std::greater> ----
3103 Worklist, Pending; 0
3104 SmallPtrSet OnWorklist, OnPending; 0
3105 ----
3106 // The set of blocks we'll be examining. ----
3107 SmallPtrSet BlocksToExplore; 0
3108 ----
3109 // The order in which to examine them (RPO). ----
3110 SmallVector BlockOrders; 0
3111 ----
3112 // RPO ordering function. ----
3113 auto Cmp = [&](MachineBasicBlock *A, MachineBasicBlock *B) { 0
3114 return BBToOrder[A] < BBToOrder[B]; 0
3115 }; 0
3116 ----
3117 getBlocksForScope(DILoc, BlocksToExplore, AssignBlocks); 0
3118 ----
3119 // Single block scope: not interesting! No propagation at all. Note that ----
3120 // this could probably go above ArtificialBlocks without damage, but ----
3121 // that then produces output differences from original-live-debug-values, ----
3122 // which propagates from a single block into many artificial ones. ----
3123 if (BlocksToExplore.size() == 1) 0
3124 return; 0
3125 ----
3126 // Convert a const set to a non-const set. LexicalScopes ----
3127 // getMachineBasicBlocks returns const MBB pointers, IDF wants mutable ones. ----
3128 // (Neither of them mutate anything). ----
3129 SmallPtrSet MutBlocksToExplore; 0
3130 for (const auto *MBB : BlocksToExplore) 0
3131 MutBlocksToExplore.insert(const_cast(MBB)); 0
3132 ----
3133 // Picks out relevants blocks RPO order and sort them. ----
3134 for (const auto *MBB : BlocksToExplore) 0
3135 BlockOrders.push_back(const_cast(MBB)); 0
3136 ----
3137 llvm::sort(BlockOrders, Cmp); 0
3138 unsigned NumBlocks = BlockOrders.size(); 0
3139 ----
3140 // Allocate some vectors for storing the live ins and live outs. Large. ----
3141 SmallVector LiveIns, LiveOuts; 0
3142 LiveIns.reserve(NumBlocks); 0
3143 LiveOuts.reserve(NumBlocks); 0
3144 ----
3145 // Initialize all values to start as NoVals. This signifies "it's live ----
3146 // through, but we don't know what it is". ----
3147 DbgValueProperties EmptyProperties(EmptyExpr, false, false); 0
3148 for (unsigned int I = 0; I < NumBlocks; ++I) { 0
3149 DbgValue EmptyDbgValue(I, EmptyProperties, DbgValue::NoVal); 0
3150 LiveIns.push_back(EmptyDbgValue); 0
3151 LiveOuts.push_back(EmptyDbgValue); 0
3152 } ----
3153 ----
3154 // Produce by-MBB indexes of live-in/live-outs, to ease lookup within ----
3155 // vlocJoin. ----
3156 LiveIdxT LiveOutIdx, LiveInIdx; 0
3157 LiveOutIdx.reserve(NumBlocks); 0
3158 LiveInIdx.reserve(NumBlocks); 0
3159 for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumBlocks; ++I) { 0
3160 LiveOutIdx[BlockOrders[I]] = &LiveOuts[I]; 0
3161 LiveInIdx[BlockOrders[I]] = &LiveIns[I]; 0
3162 } ----
3163 ----
3164 // Loop over each variable and place PHIs for it, then propagate values ----
3165 // between blocks. This keeps the locality of working on one lexical scope at ----
3166 // at time, but avoids re-processing variable values because some other ----
3167 // variable has been assigned. ----
3168 for (const auto &Var : VarsWeCareAbout) { 0
3169 // Re-initialize live-ins and live-outs, to clear the remains of previous ----
3170 // variables live-ins / live-outs. ----
3171 for (unsigned int I = 0; I < NumBlocks; ++I) { 0
3172 DbgValue EmptyDbgValue(I, EmptyProperties, DbgValue::NoVal); 0
3173 LiveIns[I] = EmptyDbgValue; 0
3174 LiveOuts[I] = EmptyDbgValue; 0
3175 } ----
3176 ----
3177 // Place PHIs for variable values, using the LLVM IDF calculator. ----
3178 // Collect the set of blocks where variables are def'd. ----
3179 SmallPtrSet DefBlocks; 0
3180 for (const MachineBasicBlock *ExpMBB : BlocksToExplore) { 0
3181 auto &TransferFunc = AllTheVLocs[ExpMBB->getNumber()].Vars; 0
3182 if (TransferFunc.contains(Var)) 0
3183 DefBlocks.insert(const_cast(ExpMBB)); 0
3184 } ----
3185 ----
3186 SmallVector PHIBlocks; 0
3187 ----
3188 // Request the set of PHIs we should insert for this variable. If there's ----
3189 // only one value definition, things are very simple. ----
3190 if (DefBlocks.size() == 1) { 0
3191 placePHIsForSingleVarDefinition(MutBlocksToExplore, *DefBlocks.begin(), 0
3192 AllTheVLocs, Var, Output); ----
3193 continue; 0
3194 } ----
3195 ----
3196 // Otherwise: we need to place PHIs through SSA and propagate values. ----
3197 BlockPHIPlacement(MutBlocksToExplore, DefBlocks, PHIBlocks); 0
3198 ----
3199 // Insert PHIs into the per-block live-in tables for this variable. ----
3200 for (MachineBasicBlock *PHIMBB : PHIBlocks) { 0
3201 unsigned BlockNo = PHIMBB->getNumber(); 0
3202 DbgValue *LiveIn = LiveInIdx[PHIMBB]; 0
3203 *LiveIn = DbgValue(BlockNo, EmptyProperties, DbgValue::VPHI); 0
3204 } ----
3205 ----
3206 for (auto *MBB : BlockOrders) { 0
3207 Worklist.push(BBToOrder[MBB]); 0
3208 OnWorklist.insert(MBB); 0
3209 } ----
3210 ----
3211 // Iterate over all the blocks we selected, propagating the variables value. ----
3212 // This loop does two things: ----
3213 // * Eliminates un-necessary VPHIs in vlocJoin, ----
3214 // * Evaluates the blocks transfer function (i.e. variable assignments) and ----
3215 // stores the result to the blocks live-outs. ----
3216 // Always evaluate the transfer function on the first iteration, and when ----
3217 // the live-ins change thereafter. ----
3218 bool FirstTrip = true; 0
3219 while (!Worklist.empty() || !Pending.empty()) { 0
3220 while (!Worklist.empty()) { 0
3221 auto *MBB = OrderToBB[Worklist.top()]; 0
3222 CurBB = MBB->getNumber(); 0
3223 Worklist.pop(); 0
3224 ----
3225 auto LiveInsIt = LiveInIdx.find(MBB); 0
3226 assert(LiveInsIt != LiveInIdx.end()); 0
3227 DbgValue *LiveIn = LiveInsIt->second; 0
3228 ----
3229 // Join values from predecessors. Updates LiveInIdx, and writes output ----
3230 // into JoinedInLocs. ----
3231 bool InLocsChanged = ----
3232 vlocJoin(*MBB, LiveOutIdx, BlocksToExplore, *LiveIn); 0
3233 ----
3234 SmallVector Preds; 0
3235 for (const auto *Pred : MBB->predecessors()) 0
3236 Preds.push_back(Pred); 0
3237 ----
3238 // If this block's live-in value is a VPHI, try to pick a machine-value ----
3239 // for it. This makes the machine-value available and propagated ----
3240 // through all blocks by the time value propagation finishes. We can't ----
3241 // do this any earlier as it needs to read the block live-outs. ----
3242 if (LiveIn->Kind == DbgValue::VPHI && LiveIn->BlockNo == (int)CurBB) { 0
3243 // There's a small possibility that on a preceeding path, a VPHI is ----
3244 // eliminated and transitions from VPHI-with-location to ----
3245 // live-through-value. As a result, the selected location of any VPHI ----
3246 // might change, so we need to re-compute it on each iteration. ----
3247 SmallVector JoinedOps; 0
3248 ----
3249 if (pickVPHILoc(JoinedOps, *MBB, LiveOutIdx, MOutLocs, Preds)) { 0
3250 bool NewLocPicked = !equal(LiveIn->getDbgOpIDs(), JoinedOps); 0
3251 InLocsChanged |= NewLocPicked; 0
3252 if (NewLocPicked) 0
3253 LiveIn->setDbgOpIDs(JoinedOps); 0
3254 } ----
3255 } 0
3256 ----
3257 if (!InLocsChanged && !FirstTrip) 0
3258 continue; 0
3259 ----
3260 DbgValue *LiveOut = LiveOutIdx[MBB]; 0
3261 bool OLChanged = false; 0
3262 ----
3263 // Do transfer function. ----
3264 auto &VTracker = AllTheVLocs[MBB->getNumber()]; 0
3265 auto TransferIt = VTracker.Vars.find(Var); 0
3266 if (TransferIt != VTracker.Vars.end()) { 0
3267 // Erase on empty transfer (DBG_VALUE $noreg). ----
3268 if (TransferIt->second.Kind == DbgValue::Undef) { 0
3269 DbgValue NewVal(MBB->getNumber(), EmptyProperties, DbgValue::NoVal); 0
3270 if (*LiveOut != NewVal) { 0
3271 *LiveOut = NewVal; 0
3272 OLChanged = true; 0
3273 } ----
3274 } else { ----
3275 // Insert new variable value; or overwrite. ----
3276 if (*LiveOut != TransferIt->second) { 0
3277 *LiveOut = TransferIt->second; 0
3278 OLChanged = true; 0
3279 } ----
3280 } ----
3281 } else { ----
3282 // Just copy live-ins to live-outs, for anything not transferred. ----
3283 if (*LiveOut != *LiveIn) { 0
3284 *LiveOut = *LiveIn; 0
3285 OLChanged = true; 0
3286 } ----
3287 } ----
3288 ----
3289 // If no live-out value changed, there's no need to explore further. ----
3290 if (!OLChanged) 0
3291 continue; 0
3292 ----
3293 // We should visit all successors. Ensure we'll visit any non-backedge ----
3294 // successors during this dataflow iteration; book backedge successors ----
3295 // to be visited next time around. ----
3296 for (auto *s : MBB->successors()) { 0
3297 // Ignore out of scope / not-to-be-explored successors. ----
3298 if (!LiveInIdx.contains(s)) 0
3299 continue; 0
3300 ----
3301 if (BBToOrder[s] > BBToOrder[MBB]) { 0
3302 if (OnWorklist.insert(s).second) 0
3303 Worklist.push(BBToOrder[s]); 0
3304 } else if (OnPending.insert(s).second && (FirstTrip || OLChanged)) { 0
3305 Pending.push(BBToOrder[s]); 0
3306 } ----
3307 } ----
3308 } 0
3309 Worklist.swap(Pending); 0
3310 std::swap(OnWorklist, OnPending); 0
3311 OnPending.clear(); 0
3312 assert(Pending.empty()); 0
3313 FirstTrip = false; 0
3314 } ----
3315 ----
3316 // Save live-ins to output vector. Ignore any that are still marked as being ----
3317 // VPHIs with no location -- those are variables that we know the value of, ----
3318 // but are not actually available in the register file. ----
3319 for (auto *MBB : BlockOrders) { 0
3320 DbgValue *BlockLiveIn = LiveInIdx[MBB]; 0
3321 if (BlockLiveIn->Kind == DbgValue::NoVal) 0
3322 continue; 0
3323 if (BlockLiveIn->isUnjoinedPHI()) 0
3324 continue; 0
3325 if (BlockLiveIn->Kind == DbgValue::VPHI) 0
3326 BlockLiveIn->Kind = DbgValue::Def; 0
3327 assert(BlockLiveIn->Properties.DIExpr->getFragmentInfo() == 0
3328 Var.getFragment() && "Fragment info missing during value prop"); ----
3329 Output[MBB->getNumber()].push_back(std::make_pair(Var, *BlockLiveIn)); 0
3330 } ----
3331 } // Per-variable loop. 0
3332 ----
3333 BlockOrders.clear(); 0
3334 BlocksToExplore.clear(); 0
3335 } 0
3336 ----
3337 void InstrRefBasedLDV::placePHIsForSingleVarDefinition( 0
3338 const SmallPtrSetImpl &InScopeBlocks, ----
3339 MachineBasicBlock *AssignMBB, SmallVectorImpl &AllTheVLocs, ----
3340 const DebugVariable &Var, LiveInsT &Output) { ----
3341 // If there is a single definition of the variable, then working out it's ----
3342 // value everywhere is very simple: it's every block dominated by the ----
3343 // definition. At the dominance frontier, the usual algorithm would: ----
3344 // * Place PHIs, ----
3345 // * Propagate values into them, ----
3346 // * Find there's no incoming variable value from the other incoming branches ----
3347 // of the dominance frontier, ----
3348 // * Specify there's no variable value in blocks past the frontier. ----
3349 // This is a common case, hence it's worth special-casing it. ----
3350 ----
3351 // Pick out the variables value from the block transfer function. ----
3352 VLocTracker &VLocs = AllTheVLocs[AssignMBB->getNumber()]; 0
3353 auto ValueIt = VLocs.Vars.find(Var); 0
3354 const DbgValue &Value = ValueIt->second; 0
3355 ----
3356 // If it's an explicit assignment of "undef", that means there is no location ----
3357 // anyway, anywhere. ----
3358 if (Value.Kind == DbgValue::Undef) 0
3359 return; 0
3360 ----
3361 // Assign the variable value to entry to each dominated block that's in scope. ----
3362 // Skip the definition block -- it's assigned the variable value in the middle ----
3363 // of the block somewhere. ----
3364 for (auto *ScopeBlock : InScopeBlocks) { 0
3365 if (!DomTree->properlyDominates(AssignMBB, ScopeBlock)) 0
3366 continue; 0
3367 ----
3368 Output[ScopeBlock->getNumber()].push_back({Var, Value}); 0
3369 } ----
3370 ----
3371 // All blocks that aren't dominated have no live-in value, thus no variable ----
3372 // value will be given to them. ----
3373 } ----
3374 ----
3375 #if !defined(NDEBUG) || defined(LLVM_ENABLE_DUMP) ----
3376 void InstrRefBasedLDV::dump_mloc_transfer( 0
3377 const MLocTransferMap &mloc_transfer) const { ----
3378 for (const auto &P : mloc_transfer) { 0
3379 std::string foo = MTracker->LocIdxToName(P.first); 0
3380 std::string bar = MTracker->IDAsString(P.second); 0
3381 dbgs() << "Loc " << foo << " --> " << bar << "\n"; 0
3382 } 0
3383 } 0
3384 #endif ----
3385 ----
3386 void InstrRefBasedLDV::initialSetup(MachineFunction &MF) { 0
3387 // Build some useful data structures. ----
3388 ----
3389 LLVMContext &Context = MF.getFunction().getContext(); 0
3390 EmptyExpr = DIExpression::get(Context, {}); 0
3391 ----
3392 auto hasNonArtificialLocation = [](const MachineInstr &MI) -> bool { 0
3393 if (const DebugLoc &DL = MI.getDebugLoc()) 0
3394 return DL.getLine() != 0; 0
3395 return false; 0
3396 }; ----
3397 // Collect a set of all the artificial blocks. ----
3398 for (auto &MBB : MF) 0
3399 if (none_of(MBB.instrs(), hasNonArtificialLocation)) 0
3400 ArtificialBlocks.insert(&MBB); 0
3401 ----
3402 // Compute mappings of block <=> RPO order. ----
3403 ReversePostOrderTraversal RPOT(&MF); 0
3404 unsigned int RPONumber = 0; 0
3405 auto processMBB = [&](MachineBasicBlock *MBB) { 0
3406 OrderToBB[RPONumber] = MBB; 0
3407 BBToOrder[MBB] = RPONumber; 0
3408 BBNumToRPO[MBB->getNumber()] = RPONumber; 0
3409 ++RPONumber; 0
3410 }; 0
3411 for (MachineBasicBlock *MBB : RPOT) 0
3412 processMBB(MBB); 0
3413 for (MachineBasicBlock &MBB : MF) 0
3414 if (!BBToOrder.contains(&MBB)) 0
3415 processMBB(&MBB); 0
3416 ----
3417 // Order value substitutions by their "source" operand pair, for quick lookup. ----
3418 llvm::sort(MF.DebugValueSubstitutions); 0
3419 ----
3420 #ifdef EXPENSIVE_CHECKS ----
3421 // As an expensive check, test whether there are any duplicate substitution ----
3422 // sources in the collection. ----
3423 if (MF.DebugValueSubstitutions.size() > 2) { ----
3424 for (auto It = MF.DebugValueSubstitutions.begin(); ----
3425 It != std::prev(MF.DebugValueSubstitutions.end()); ++It) { ----
3426 assert(It->Src != std::next(It)->Src && "Duplicate variable location " ----
3427 "substitution seen"); ----
3428 } ----
3429 } ----
3430 #endif ----
3431 } 0
3432 ----
3433 // Produce an "ejection map" for blocks, i.e., what's the highest-numbered ----
3434 // lexical scope it's used in. When exploring in DFS order and we pass that ----
3435 // scope, the block can be processed and any tracking information freed. ----
3436 void InstrRefBasedLDV::makeDepthFirstEjectionMap( 0
3437 SmallVectorImpl &EjectionMap, ----
3438 const ScopeToDILocT &ScopeToDILocation, ----
3439 ScopeToAssignBlocksT &ScopeToAssignBlocks) { ----
3440 SmallPtrSet BlocksToExplore; 0
3441 SmallVector, 4> WorkStack; 0
3442 auto *TopScope = LS.getCurrentFunctionScope(); 0
3443 ----
3444 // Unlike lexical scope explorers, we explore in reverse order, to find the ----
3445 // "last" lexical scope used for each block early. ----
3446 WorkStack.push_back({TopScope, TopScope->getChildren().size() - 1}); 0
3447 ----
3448 while (!WorkStack.empty()) { 0
3449 auto &ScopePosition = WorkStack.back(); 0
3450 LexicalScope *WS = ScopePosition.first; 0
3451 ssize_t ChildNum = ScopePosition.second--; 0
3452 ----
3453 const SmallVectorImpl &Children = WS->getChildren(); 0
3454 if (ChildNum >= 0) { 0
3455 // If ChildNum is positive, there are remaining children to explore. ----
3456 // Push the child and its children-count onto the stack. ----
3457 auto &ChildScope = Children[ChildNum]; 0
3458 WorkStack.push_back( 0
3459 std::make_pair(ChildScope, ChildScope->getChildren().size() - 1)); 0
3460 } else { ----
3461 WorkStack.pop_back(); 0
3462 ----
3463 // We've explored all children and any later blocks: examine all blocks ----
3464 // in our scope. If they haven't yet had an ejection number set, then ----
3465 // this scope will be the last to use that block. ----
3466 auto DILocationIt = ScopeToDILocation.find(WS); 0
3467 if (DILocationIt != ScopeToDILocation.end()) { 0
3468 getBlocksForScope(DILocationIt->second, BlocksToExplore, 0
3469 ScopeToAssignBlocks.find(WS)->second); 0
3470 for (const auto *MBB : BlocksToExplore) { 0
3471 unsigned BBNum = MBB->getNumber(); 0
3472 if (EjectionMap[BBNum] == 0) 0
3473 EjectionMap[BBNum] = WS->getDFSOut(); 0
3474 } ----
3475 ----
3476 BlocksToExplore.clear(); 0
3477 } ----
3478 } ----
3479 } ----
3480 } 0
3481 ----
3482 bool InstrRefBasedLDV::depthFirstVLocAndEmit( 0
3483 unsigned MaxNumBlocks, const ScopeToDILocT &ScopeToDILocation, ----
3484 const ScopeToVarsT &ScopeToVars, ScopeToAssignBlocksT &ScopeToAssignBlocks, ----
3485 LiveInsT &Output, FuncValueTable &MOutLocs, FuncValueTable &MInLocs, ----
3486 SmallVectorImpl &AllTheVLocs, MachineFunction &MF, ----
3487 DenseMap &AllVarsNumbering, ----
3488 const TargetPassConfig &TPC) { ----
3489 TTracker = new TransferTracker(TII, MTracker, MF, *TRI, CalleeSavedRegs, TPC); 0
3490 unsigned NumLocs = MTracker->getNumLocs(); 0
3491 VTracker = nullptr; 0
3492 ----
3493 // No scopes? No variable locations. ----
3494 if (!LS.getCurrentFunctionScope()) 0
3495 return false; 0
3496 ----
3497 // Build map from block number to the last scope that uses the block. ----
3498 SmallVector EjectionMap; 0
3499 EjectionMap.resize(MaxNumBlocks, 0); 0
3500 makeDepthFirstEjectionMap(EjectionMap, ScopeToDILocation, 0
3501 ScopeToAssignBlocks); ----
3502 ----
3503 // Helper lambda for ejecting a block -- if nothing is going to use the block, ----
3504 // we can translate the variable location information into DBG_VALUEs and then ----
3505 // free all of InstrRefBasedLDV's data structures. ----
3506 auto EjectBlock = [&](MachineBasicBlock &MBB) -> void { 0
3507 unsigned BBNum = MBB.getNumber(); 0
3508 AllTheVLocs[BBNum].clear(); 0
3509 ----
3510 // Prime the transfer-tracker, and then step through all the block ----
3511 // instructions, installing transfers. ----
3512 MTracker->reset(); 0
3513 MTracker->loadFromArray(MInLocs[BBNum], BBNum); 0
3514 TTracker->loadInlocs(MBB, MInLocs[BBNum], DbgOpStore, Output[BBNum], 0
3515 NumLocs); 0
3516 ----
3517 CurBB = BBNum; 0
3518 CurInst = 1; 0
3519 for (auto &MI : MBB) { 0
3520 process(MI, MOutLocs.get(), MInLocs.get()); 0
3521 TTracker->checkInstForNewValues(CurInst, MI.getIterator()); 0
3522 ++CurInst; 0
3523 } ----
3524 ----
3525 // Free machine-location tables for this block. ----
3526 MInLocs[BBNum].reset(); 0
3527 MOutLocs[BBNum].reset(); 0
3528 // We don't need live-in variable values for this block either. ----
3529 Output[BBNum].clear(); 0
3530 AllTheVLocs[BBNum].clear(); 0
3531 }; 0
3532 ----
3533 SmallPtrSet BlocksToExplore; 0
3534 SmallVector, 4> WorkStack; 0
3535 WorkStack.push_back({LS.getCurrentFunctionScope(), 0}); 0
3536 unsigned HighestDFSIn = 0; 0
3537 ----
3538 // Proceed to explore in depth first order. ----
3539 while (!WorkStack.empty()) { 0
3540 auto &ScopePosition = WorkStack.back(); 0
3541 LexicalScope *WS = ScopePosition.first; 0
3542 ssize_t ChildNum = ScopePosition.second++; 0
3543 ----
3544 // We obesrve scopes with children twice here, once descending in, once ----
3545 // ascending out of the scope nest. Use HighestDFSIn as a ratchet to ensure ----
3546 // we don't process a scope twice. Additionally, ignore scopes that don't ----
3547 // have a DILocation -- by proxy, this means we never tracked any variable ----
3548 // assignments in that scope. ----
3549 auto DILocIt = ScopeToDILocation.find(WS); 0
3550 if (HighestDFSIn <= WS->getDFSIn() && DILocIt != ScopeToDILocation.end()) { 0
3551 const DILocation *DILoc = DILocIt->second; 0
3552 auto &VarsWeCareAbout = ScopeToVars.find(WS)->second; 0
3553 auto &BlocksInScope = ScopeToAssignBlocks.find(WS)->second; 0
3554 ----
3555 buildVLocValueMap(DILoc, VarsWeCareAbout, BlocksInScope, Output, MOutLocs, 0
3556 MInLocs, AllTheVLocs); ----
3557 } ----
3558 ----
3559 HighestDFSIn = std::max(HighestDFSIn, WS->getDFSIn()); 0
3560 ----
3561 // Descend into any scope nests. ----
3562 const SmallVectorImpl &Children = WS->getChildren(); 0
3563 if (ChildNum < (ssize_t)Children.size()) { 0
3564 // There are children to explore -- push onto stack and continue. ----
3565 auto &ChildScope = Children[ChildNum]; 0
3566 WorkStack.push_back(std::make_pair(ChildScope, 0)); 0
3567 } else { ----
3568 WorkStack.pop_back(); 0
3569 ----
3570 // We've explored a leaf, or have explored all the children of a scope. ----
3571 // Try to eject any blocks where this is the last scope it's relevant to. ----
3572 auto DILocationIt = ScopeToDILocation.find(WS); 0
3573 if (DILocationIt == ScopeToDILocation.end()) 0
3574 continue; 0
3575 ----
3576 getBlocksForScope(DILocationIt->second, BlocksToExplore, 0
3577 ScopeToAssignBlocks.find(WS)->second); 0
3578 for (const auto *MBB : BlocksToExplore) 0
3579 if (WS->getDFSOut() == EjectionMap[MBB->getNumber()]) 0
3580 EjectBlock(const_cast(*MBB)); 0
3581 ----
3582 BlocksToExplore.clear(); 0
3583 } ----
3584 } ----
3585 ----
3586 // Some artificial blocks may not have been ejected, meaning they're not ----
3587 // connected to an actual legitimate scope. This can technically happen ----
3588 // with things like the entry block. In theory, we shouldn't need to do ----
3589 // anything for such out-of-scope blocks, but for the sake of being similar ----
3590 // to VarLocBasedLDV, eject these too. ----
3591 for (auto *MBB : ArtificialBlocks) 0
3592 if (MOutLocs[MBB->getNumber()]) 0
3593 EjectBlock(*MBB); 0
3594 ----
3595 return emitTransfers(AllVarsNumbering); 0
3596 } 0
3597 ----
3598 bool InstrRefBasedLDV::emitTransfers( 0
3599 DenseMap &AllVarsNumbering) { ----
3600 // Go through all the transfers recorded in the TransferTracker -- this is ----
3601 // both the live-ins to a block, and any movements of values that happen ----
3602 // in the middle. ----
3603 for (const auto &P : TTracker->Transfers) { 0
3604 // We have to insert DBG_VALUEs in a consistent order, otherwise they ----
3605 // appear in DWARF in different orders. Use the order that they appear ----
3606 // when walking through each block / each instruction, stored in ----
3607 // AllVarsNumbering. ----
3608 SmallVector> Insts; 0
3609 for (MachineInstr *MI : P.Insts) { 0
3610 DebugVariable Var(MI->getDebugVariable(), MI->getDebugExpression(), ----
3611 MI->getDebugLoc()->getInlinedAt()); 0
3612 Insts.emplace_back(AllVarsNumbering.find(Var)->second, MI); 0
3613 } ----
3614 llvm::sort(Insts, llvm::less_first()); 0
3615 ----
3616 // Insert either before or after the designated point... ----
3617 if (P.MBB) { 0
3618 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *P.MBB; 0
3619 for (const auto &Pair : Insts) 0
3620 MBB.insert(P.Pos, Pair.second); 0
3621 } else { ----
3622 // Terminators, like tail calls, can clobber things. Don't try and place ----
3623 // transfers after them. ----
3624 if (P.Pos->isTerminator()) 0
3625 continue; 0
3626 ----
3627 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *P.Pos->getParent(); 0
3628 for (const auto &Pair : Insts) 0
3629 MBB.insertAfterBundle(P.Pos, Pair.second); 0
3630 } ----
3631 } 0
3632 ----
3633 return TTracker->Transfers.size() != 0; 0
3634 } ----
3635 ----
3636 /// Calculate the liveness information for the given machine function and ----
3637 /// extend ranges across basic blocks. ----
3638 bool InstrRefBasedLDV::ExtendRanges(MachineFunction &MF, 0
3639 MachineDominatorTree *DomTree, ----
3640 TargetPassConfig *TPC, ----
3641 unsigned InputBBLimit, ----
3642 unsigned InputDbgValLimit) { ----
3643 // No subprogram means this function contains no debuginfo. ----
3644 if (!MF.getFunction().getSubprogram()) 0
3645 return false; 0
3646 ----
3647 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\nDebug Range Extension\n"); 0
3648 this->TPC = TPC; 0
3649 ----
3650 this->DomTree = DomTree; 0
3651 TRI = MF.getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo(); 0
3652 MRI = &MF.getRegInfo(); 0
3653 TII = MF.getSubtarget().getInstrInfo(); 0
3654 TFI = MF.getSubtarget().getFrameLowering(); 0
3655 TFI->getCalleeSaves(MF, CalleeSavedRegs); 0
3656 MFI = &MF.getFrameInfo(); 0
3657 LS.initialize(MF); 0
3658 ----
3659 const auto &STI = MF.getSubtarget(); 0
3660 AdjustsStackInCalls = MFI->adjustsStack() && 0
3661 STI.getFrameLowering()->stackProbeFunctionModifiesSP(); 0
3662 if (AdjustsStackInCalls) 0
3663 StackProbeSymbolName = STI.getTargetLowering()->getStackProbeSymbolName(MF); 0
3664 ----
3665 MTracker = 0
3666 new MLocTracker(MF, *TII, *TRI, *MF.getSubtarget().getTargetLowering()); 0
3667 VTracker = nullptr; 0
3668 TTracker = nullptr; 0
3669 ----
3670 SmallVector MLocTransfer; 0
3671 SmallVector vlocs; 0
3672 LiveInsT SavedLiveIns; 0
3673 ----
3674 int MaxNumBlocks = -1; 0
3675 for (auto &MBB : MF) 0
3676 MaxNumBlocks = std::max(MBB.getNumber(), MaxNumBlocks); 0
3677 assert(MaxNumBlocks >= 0); 0
3678 ++MaxNumBlocks; 0
3679 ----
3680 initialSetup(MF); 0
3681 ----
3682 MLocTransfer.resize(MaxNumBlocks); 0
3683 vlocs.resize(MaxNumBlocks, VLocTracker(OverlapFragments, EmptyExpr)); 0
3684 SavedLiveIns.resize(MaxNumBlocks); 0
3685 ----
3686 produceMLocTransferFunction(MF, MLocTransfer, MaxNumBlocks); 0
3687 ----
3688 // Allocate and initialize two array-of-arrays for the live-in and live-out ----
3689 // machine values. The outer dimension is the block number; while the inner ----
3690 // dimension is a LocIdx from MLocTracker. ----
3691 FuncValueTable MOutLocs = std::make_unique(MaxNumBlocks); 0
3692 FuncValueTable MInLocs = std::make_unique(MaxNumBlocks); 0
3693 unsigned NumLocs = MTracker->getNumLocs(); 0
3694 for (int i = 0; i < MaxNumBlocks; ++i) { 0
3695 // These all auto-initialize to ValueIDNum::EmptyValue ----
3696 MOutLocs[i] = std::make_unique(NumLocs); 0
3697 MInLocs[i] = std::make_unique(NumLocs); 0
3698 } ----
3699 ----
3700 // Solve the machine value dataflow problem using the MLocTransfer function, ----
3701 // storing the computed live-ins / live-outs into the array-of-arrays. We use ----
3702 // both live-ins and live-outs for decision making in the variable value ----
3703 // dataflow problem. ----
3704 buildMLocValueMap(MF, MInLocs, MOutLocs, MLocTransfer); 0
3705 ----
3706 // Patch up debug phi numbers, turning unknown block-live-in values into ----
3707 // either live-through machine values, or PHIs. ----
3708 for (auto &DBG_PHI : DebugPHINumToValue) { 0
3709 // Identify unresolved block-live-ins. ----
3710 if (!DBG_PHI.ValueRead) 0
3711 continue; 0
3712 ----
3713 ValueIDNum &Num = *DBG_PHI.ValueRead; 0
3714 if (!Num.isPHI()) 0
3715 continue; 0
3716 ----
3717 unsigned BlockNo = Num.getBlock(); 0
3718 LocIdx LocNo = Num.getLoc(); 0
3719 ValueIDNum ResolvedValue = MInLocs[BlockNo][LocNo.asU64()]; 0
3720 // If there is no resolved value for this live-in then it is not directly ----
3721 // reachable from the entry block -- model it as a PHI on entry to this ----
3722 // block, which means we leave the ValueIDNum unchanged. ----
3723 if (ResolvedValue != ValueIDNum::EmptyValue) 0
3724 Num = ResolvedValue; 0
3725 } ----
3726 // Later, we'll be looking up ranges of instruction numbers. ----
3727 llvm::sort(DebugPHINumToValue); 0
3728 ----
3729 // Walk back through each block / instruction, collecting DBG_VALUE ----
3730 // instructions and recording what machine value their operands refer to. ----
3731 for (auto &OrderPair : OrderToBB) { 0
3732 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *OrderPair.second; 0
3733 CurBB = MBB.getNumber(); 0
3734 VTracker = &vlocs[CurBB]; 0
3735 VTracker->MBB = &MBB; 0
3736 MTracker->loadFromArray(MInLocs[CurBB], CurBB); 0
3737 CurInst = 1; 0
3738 for (auto &MI : MBB) { 0
3739 process(MI, MOutLocs.get(), MInLocs.get()); 0
3740 ++CurInst; 0
3741 } ----
3742 MTracker->reset(); 0
3743 } ----
3744 ----
3745 // Number all variables in the order that they appear, to be used as a stable ----
3746 // insertion order later. ----
3747 DenseMap AllVarsNumbering; 0
3748 ----
3749 // Map from one LexicalScope to all the variables in that scope. ----
3750 ScopeToVarsT ScopeToVars; 0
3751 ----
3752 // Map from One lexical scope to all blocks where assignments happen for ----
3753 // that scope. ----
3754 ScopeToAssignBlocksT ScopeToAssignBlocks; 0
3755 ----
3756 // Store map of DILocations that describes scopes. ----
3757 ScopeToDILocT ScopeToDILocation; 0
3758 ----
3759 // To mirror old LiveDebugValues, enumerate variables in RPOT order. Otherwise ----
3760 // the order is unimportant, it just has to be stable. ----
3761 unsigned VarAssignCount = 0; 0
3762 for (unsigned int I = 0; I < OrderToBB.size(); ++I) { 0
3763 auto *MBB = OrderToBB[I]; 0
3764 auto *VTracker = &vlocs[MBB->getNumber()]; 0
3765 // Collect each variable with a DBG_VALUE in this block. ----
3766 for (auto &idx : VTracker->Vars) { 0
3767 const auto &Var = idx.first; 0
3768 const DILocation *ScopeLoc = VTracker->Scopes[Var]; 0
3769 assert(ScopeLoc != nullptr); 0
3770 auto *Scope = LS.findLexicalScope(ScopeLoc); 0
3771 ----
3772 // No insts in scope -> shouldn't have been recorded. ----
3773 assert(Scope != nullptr); 0
3774 ----
3775 AllVarsNumbering.insert(std::make_pair(Var, AllVarsNumbering.size())); 0
3776 ScopeToVars[Scope].insert(Var); 0
3777 ScopeToAssignBlocks[Scope].insert(VTracker->MBB); 0
3778 ScopeToDILocation[Scope] = ScopeLoc; 0
3779 ++VarAssignCount; 0
3780 } ----
3781 } ----
3782 ----
3783 bool Changed = false; 0
3784 ----
3785 // If we have an extremely large number of variable assignments and blocks, ----
3786 // bail out at this point. We've burnt some time doing analysis already, ----
3787 // however we should cut our losses. ----
3788 if ((unsigned)MaxNumBlocks > InputBBLimit && 0
3789 VarAssignCount > InputDbgValLimit) { ----
3790 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Disabling InstrRefBasedLDV: " << MF.getName() 0
3791 << " has " << MaxNumBlocks << " basic blocks and " ----
3792 << VarAssignCount ----
3793 << " variable assignments, exceeding limits.\n"); ----
3794 } else { ----
3795 // Optionally, solve the variable value problem and emit to blocks by using ----
3796 // a lexical-scope-depth search. It should be functionally identical to ----
3797 // the "else" block of this condition. ----
3798 Changed = depthFirstVLocAndEmit( 0
3799 MaxNumBlocks, ScopeToDILocation, ScopeToVars, ScopeToAssignBlocks, ----
3800 SavedLiveIns, MOutLocs, MInLocs, vlocs, MF, AllVarsNumbering, *TPC); ----
3801 } ----
3802 ----
3803 delete MTracker; 0
3804 delete TTracker; 0
3805 MTracker = nullptr; 0
3806 VTracker = nullptr; 0
3807 TTracker = nullptr; 0
3808 ----
3809 ArtificialBlocks.clear(); 0
3810 OrderToBB.clear(); 0
3811 BBToOrder.clear(); 0
3812 BBNumToRPO.clear(); 0
3813 DebugInstrNumToInstr.clear(); 0
3814 DebugPHINumToValue.clear(); 0
3815 OverlapFragments.clear(); 0
3816 SeenFragments.clear(); 0
3817 SeenDbgPHIs.clear(); 0
3818 DbgOpStore.clear(); 0
3819 ----
3820 return Changed; 0
3821 } 0

3824 return new InstrRefBasedLDV(); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
3825 } ----

3831 // Pick a type to identify incoming block values as we construct SSA. We ----
3832 // can't use anything more robust than an integer unfortunately, as SSAUpdater ----
3833 // expects to zero-initialize the type. ----
3834 typedef uint64_t BlockValueNum; ----
3835 ----
3836 /// Represents an SSA PHI node for the SSA updater class. Contains the block ----
3837 /// this PHI is in, the value number it would have, and the expected incoming ----
3838 /// values from parent blocks. ----
3839 class LDVSSAPhi { ----
3840 public: ----
3841 SmallVector, 4> IncomingValues; ----
3842 LDVSSABlock *ParentBlock; ----
3843 BlockValueNum PHIValNum; ----
3844 LDVSSAPhi(BlockValueNum PHIValNum, LDVSSABlock *ParentBlock) 0
3845 : ParentBlock(ParentBlock), PHIValNum(PHIValNum) {} 0
3846 ----
3847 LDVSSABlock *getParent() { return ParentBlock; } 0
3848 }; ----

3850 /// Thin wrapper around a block predecessor iterator. Only difference from a ----
3851 /// normal block iterator is that it dereferences to an LDVSSABlock. ----
3852 class LDVSSABlockIterator { ----
3853 public: ----
3854 MachineBasicBlock::pred_iterator PredIt; ----
3855 LDVSSAUpdater &Updater; ----
3856 ----
3857 LDVSSABlockIterator(MachineBasicBlock::pred_iterator PredIt, 0
3858 LDVSSAUpdater &Updater) ----
3859 : PredIt(PredIt), Updater(Updater) {} 0
3860 ----
3861 bool operator!=(const LDVSSABlockIterator &OtherIt) const { 0
3862 return OtherIt.PredIt != PredIt; 0
3863 } ----
3864 ----
3865 LDVSSABlockIterator &operator++() { 0
3866 ++PredIt; 0
3867 return *this; 0
3868 } ----
3869 ----
3870 LDVSSABlock *operator*(); ----
3871 }; ----
3872 ----
3873 /// Thin wrapper around a block for SSA Updater interface. Necessary because ----
3874 /// we need to track the PHI value(s) that we may have observed as necessary ----
3875 /// in this block. ----
3876 class LDVSSABlock { ----
3877 public: ----

3880 using PHIListT = SmallVector; ----

3882 PHIListT PHIList; ----
3883 ----
3884 LDVSSABlock(MachineBasicBlock &BB, LDVSSAUpdater &Updater) 0
3885 : BB(BB), Updater(Updater) {} 0
3886 ----

3888 return LDVSSABlockIterator(BB.succ_begin(), Updater); 0
3889 } ----
3890 ----
3891 LDVSSABlockIterator succ_end() { 0
3892 return LDVSSABlockIterator(BB.succ_end(), Updater); 0
3893 } ----

3895 /// SSAUpdater has requested a PHI: create that within this block record. ----
3896 LDVSSAPhi *newPHI(BlockValueNum Value) { 0
3897 PHIList.emplace_back(Value, this); 0
3898 return &PHIList.back(); 0
3899 } ----
3900 ----
3901 /// SSAUpdater wishes to know what PHIs already exist in this block. ----
3902 PHIListT &phis() { return PHIList; } 0
3903 }; ----

3905 /// Utility class for the SSAUpdater interface: tracks blocks, PHIs and values ----
3906 /// while SSAUpdater is exploring the CFG. It's passed as a handle / baton to ----
3907 // SSAUpdaterTraits. ----
3908 class LDVSSAUpdater { ----
3909 public: ----
3910 /// Map of value numbers to PHI records. ----
3911 DenseMap PHIs; ----
3912 /// Map of which blocks generate Undef values -- blocks that are not ----
3913 /// dominated by any Def. ----
3914 DenseMap UndefMap; ----
3915 /// Map of machine blocks to our own records of them. ----
3916 DenseMap BlockMap; ----
3917 /// Machine location where any PHI must occur. ----
3918 LocIdx Loc; ----
3919 /// Table of live-in machine value numbers for blocks / locations. ----
3920 const ValueTable *MLiveIns; ----
3921 ----
3922 LDVSSAUpdater(LocIdx L, const ValueTable *MLiveIns) 0
3923 : Loc(L), MLiveIns(MLiveIns) {} 0
3924 ----
3925 void reset() { 0
3926 for (auto &Block : BlockMap) 0
3927 delete Block.second; 0
3928 ----
3929 PHIs.clear(); 0
3930 UndefMap.clear(); 0
3931 BlockMap.clear(); 0
3932 } 0
3933 ----
3934 ~LDVSSAUpdater() { reset(); } 0

3936 /// For a given MBB, create a wrapper block for it. Stores it in the ----
3937 /// LDVSSAUpdater block map. ----
3938 LDVSSABlock *getSSALDVBlock(MachineBasicBlock *BB) { 0
3939 auto it = BlockMap.find(BB); 0
3940 if (it == BlockMap.end()) { 0
3941 BlockMap[BB] = new LDVSSABlock(*BB, *this); 0
3942 it = BlockMap.find(BB); 0
3943 } ----
3944 return it->second; 0
3945 } ----
3946 ----
3947 /// Find the live-in value number for the given block. Looks up the value at ----
3948 /// the PHI location on entry. ----
3949 BlockValueNum getValue(LDVSSABlock *LDVBB) { 0
3950 return MLiveIns[LDVBB->BB.getNumber()][Loc.asU64()].asU64(); 0
3951 } ----

4021 Preds->push_back(BB->Updater.getSSALDVBlock(Pred)); 0
